Ataraxia Oc-serv.name: Ataraxia Oc-serv
Ataraxia Oc-serv.notes: Found at top of Talon Rock

Awakened Liceor.name: Awakened Liceor
Awakened Liceor.notes: Found at [Rising Particles]: replaces Dazzling Crahla

Blitz Simius.name: Blitz Simius
Blitz Simius.notes: Found at [5:00~19:00]: 116 on the rocks directly NE, where Hayreddin sleeps

Cage Saltat.name: Cage Saltat
Cage Saltat.notes: Found at [Clear]: randomly replaces Gypsy Saltats

Crater Saltat.name: Crater Saltat
Crater Saltat.notes: Found at [Clear]: randomly replaces Gypsy Saltats

Dadan Orchestra Members ?.name: Dadan Orchestra Members ?
Dadan Orchestra Members ?.notes: Found at summoned by Dadan at low health

Daimyo Ictus.name: Daimyo Ictus
Daimyo Ictus.notes: Found at M'Gando - Outside the Bestial Utopia entrance

Dim Saltat.name: Dim Saltat
Dim Saltat.notes: Found at [Clear]: randomly replaces Strange Saltats

Alexei, the Jade.name: Alexei, the Jade
Alexei, the Jade.notes: "Alexei, the Jade" can be found resting just up the hill a short distance to the north west of Lake Ciel in Sylvalum.

Celedonio, the Battle-Tested.name: Celedonio, the Battle-Tested
Celedonio, the Battle-Tested.notes: "Celedonio, the Battle-Tested" can be found resting at the north western part of Keegan Ridge in central Oblivia.

Drake, the Waypost.name: Drake, the Waypost
Drake, the Waypost.notes: "Drake, the Waypost" stands in a deep crack underneath the north end of the Elephants Trunk bridge in Noctilum.

Enhanced Search Zig.name: Enhanced Search Zig
Enhanced Search Zig.notes: "Enhanced Search Zig" guards one of the infantry towers at Wildcat Fortress south east of Scholes Battlegrounds in Cauldros. It is one of the last enemies to load into the area so it takes a moment to appear.

Unlimited Output Zig.name: Unlimited Output Zig
Unlimited Output Zig.notes: "Unlimited Output Zig" is part of a heavy concentration of forces that defends a path along the cliff between the ocean and lava to the south of Dragonbone Promontory (close to the ternion fork basecamp). Alternatively head directly north from the center of Slavebird Isle.

Brandys, the Spectral Light.name: Brandys, the Spectral Light
Brandys, the Spectral Light.notes: "Brandys, the Spectral Light" is one of several tyrants that reside within behemoth's shadows, an expansive cavern accessible above Sylvalum Searoad to the east of Sylvalum (at FN Site 420). It rarely spawns in place of another Xiphias, simply move into the next room and double back until Brandys appears in the middle of the watery room.

Belenguer, the Gunhammer.name: Belenguer, the Gunhammer
Belenguer, the Gunhammer.notes: "Belenguer, the Gunhammer" can be found near some of the bonelike rocks above King's Falls in Oblivia.

Wenzel, the Inebriated.name: Wenzel, the Inebriated
Wenzel, the Inebriated.notes: "Wenzel, the Inebriated" is up the top of the mountain directly to the south of Aaroy Plain in central Oblivia. Easy to kill. Flight required.

Goliath, the Stronghold.name: Goliath, the Stronghold
Goliath, the Stronghold.notes: "Goliath, the Stronghold" can be seen sitting down in the north cinderdunes to the north east of Anvil Sandplain in the northern tip of Sylvalum.

Sviatoslav, the Reproachful.name: Sviatoslav, the Reproachful
Sviatoslav, the Reproachful.notes: "Sviatoslav, the Reproachful" appears in the south east of Bardarich Desert during rainy weather. Fast travelling will randomise the weather on each trip. Can reflect Ether attacks.

Man'an, the Water Whisperer.name: Man'an, the Water Whisperer
Man'an, the Water Whisperer.notes: "Man'an, the Water Whisperer" is walking around on the shore at the north east corner of Lake Ciel in Sylvalum. The nearby Cerulean Arenatects will join in the fight.

Hephaestus, the Absconder.name: Hephaestus, the Absconder
Hephaestus, the Absconder.notes: "Hephaestus, the Absconder" appears during the night just north of East Gate Plain in Primordia under the rocky roof area with the water (in the Roof Rock segment).

Etutanne, the Bloodthirsty.name: Etutanne, the Bloodthirsty
Etutanne, the Bloodthirsty.notes: "Etutanne, the Bloodthirsty" can be seen in the air as it hovers above the swampy pit that is Silent Mire in east Primordia.

Manuelita, the Affectionate.name: Manuelita, the Affectionate
Manuelita, the Affectionate.notes: "Manuelita, the Affectionate" can be found relaxing in the middle island in middle Hushflood in north west Noctilum.

Katerina, the Cliffhanger.name: Katerina, the Cliffhanger
Katerina, the Cliffhanger.notes: "Katerina, the Cliffhanger" is a large white flower that is surprisingly not near a cliff but rather has planted itself on a small island in the middle level of Everwhelm falls directly to the west of Qing Long Glade in Noctilum.

Na-mulk, the Rebellious.name: Na-mulk, the Rebellious
Na-mulk, the Rebellious.notes: "Na-mulk, the Rebellious" lies dormant on the floor along the rubble close to the spiked building in the Ruined City of O'rrh Sim area in the north of Cauldros.

Legato, the Sky Watcher.name: Legato, the Sky Watcher
Legato, the Sky Watcher.notes: "Legato, the Sky Watcher" is one of several tyrants that reside within behemoth's shadows, an expansive cavern accessible above Sylvalum Searoad to the east of Sylvalum (at FN Site 420).

Caranau, the Water Drake.name: Caranau, the Water Drake
Caranau, the Water Drake.notes: "Caranau, the Water Drake" can be found in the middle of a small lake to the south of Stickstone Rise in the north west corner of Primordia. The water is deep so a character capable of using a Sniper Rifle may be needed to begin and lure it to shore in order to fight it on foot.

Gadaf's Qmoeva.name: Gadaf's Qmoeva
Gadaf's Qmoeva.notes: "Gadaf's Qmoeva" waits in the shadows on the largest tropical island between Primordia and Sylvalum.

Griffus, the Tartarean.name: Griffus, the Tartarean
Griffus, the Tartarean.notes: "Griffus, the Tartarean" can be found pacing back and forth up on the high ridge north east of Qing Long Glade in central Noctilum.

Atreides, the Distinguished.name: Atreides, the Distinguished
Atreides, the Distinguished.notes: "Atreides, the Distinguished" can be seen leaping high into the sky during the day in the northern half of Sylvalum. During the night it waits with its mouth open like a giant and highly suspicious spiked dinner plate in the sand for unsuspecting prey to move to the middle. Will call for his mate Gesserith when at low health which brings a second giant worm into the battle.

Sheldon, the Dentally Challenged.name: Sheldon, the Dentally Challenged
Sheldon, the Dentally Challenged.notes: "Sheldon, the Dentally Challenged" can be found along a tight passageway to the east of Keegan Ridge in eastern Oblivia (or to the west of Central Ibra Ravine).

Oskar, the Summer Squall.name: Oskar, the Summer Squall
Oskar, the Summer Squall.notes: "Oskar, the Summer Squall" is at the Old Dragon Tree in southern Noctilum. Like other deer type creatures it has a lot of health for its level.

Ferdinand, the Fortuitus.name: Ferdinand, the Fortuitus
Ferdinand, the Fortuitus.notes: "Ferdinand, the Fortuitus"  is joyfully rolling around in the shadows of a bone filled passage near Lake Basel in Oblivia.

Barnabas, the Despot.name: Barnabas, the Despot
Barnabas, the Despot.notes: "Barnabas, the Despot" freely runs around Oblivias Aaroy Plain during the day covering a large area between FN Sites 304, 306 and 309. Starts from Cliffside Camp, the high level ganglion outpost.

Megatonne, the Hell Express.name: Megatonne, the Hell Express
Megatonne, the Hell Express.notes: "Megatonne, the Hell Express" is a big piggy that can be found on the long dirt road around halfway between Biahno Hills and Grieving Plains in north west Primordia.

Ahama's Seidr.name: Ahama's Seidr
Ahama's Seidr.notes: "Ahama's Seidr" appears at night on an overhanging rock shelf to the north east of Anvil Sandplain in the northern half of Sylvalum.

Duran, the Draconian.name: Duran, the Draconian
Duran, the Draconian.notes: "Duran, the Draconian" commands a pack of Caro (including the tyrant Caro Spaniel, the Obedient) during the day and into part of the night. They can be found just north of T'phnom Shelf in Cauldros.

Vendura, the Spellbinder.name: Vendura, the Spellbinder
Vendura, the Spellbinder.notes: "Vendura, the Spellbinder" is up on the high ridge not too far from FN Site 303 in Oblivia. She will only be here during the day, at night she will pilot her Galdr at another location.

Go-rha, the Guardian Deity.name: Go-rha, the Guardian Deity
Go-rha, the Guardian Deity.notes: "Go-rha, the Guardian Deity" lays dormant in south Noctilums lake.

Clemente, the Iron Meteor.name: Clemente, the Iron Meteor
Clemente, the Iron Meteor.notes: "Clemente, the Iron Meteor" hides in the ground at the northern tip of Canopied Nightwood just next to the calm waters.

Ya-rhat, the Thundercloud.name: Ya-rhat, the Thundercloud
Ya-rhat, the Thundercloud.notes: "Ya-rhat, the Thundercloud" hangs around Cauldros' eastern cliffs, the Kw'arah Cloister, which is home to many mechanoids including two Xe-doms. It will suddenly appear and hover just above a strange building opposite the sitting Xe-dom.

Lambert, the Divine Wind.name: Lambert, the Divine Wind
Lambert, the Divine Wind.notes: "Lambert, the Divine Wind" runs back and forth along a small stretch of narrow path west of Humdrum Peaks in southern Noctilum.

Eliane, the Unmoved.name: Eliane, the Unmoved
Eliane, the Unmoved.notes: "Eliane, the Unmoved" is a large pink flower hiding in the ground by a ridge line just north of Balance Rock basecamp (the camp sits near the river in the east of Bardarich Desert).

Enhanced Support Zig.name: Enhanced Support Zig
Enhanced Support Zig.notes: "Enhanced Support Zig" protects a teleporter along with two other Zigs and other minor mechanoids in the middle of Dragonbone Promontory in central Cauldros. The teleporter leads to the UFO directly above it.

Air Support Galdr.name: Air Support Galdr
Air Support Galdr.notes: "Air Support Galdr" guards the night time airspace around wildcat fortress south east of Scholes Battlegrounds in Cauldros.

Muruse, the Opulent.name: Muruse, the Opulent
Muruse, the Opulent.notes: "Muruse, the Opulent" is a golden Blatta clinging to a wall in the secret passage in vitriol cesspool, a cave near FN Site 209 in the west side of Noctilum. The passage within vitriol cesspool is to the left in a crack near the fishy Purgovents. Muruse is high up on a wall to the right about halfway through this long tunnel, not at the end of it.

Intermediate Arsenal Qmoeva.name: Intermediate Arsenal Qmoeva
Intermediate Arsenal Qmoeva.notes: "Intermediate Arsenal Qmoeva" can be found at night on top of the stone roof above Silent Mire in north east Primordia.

Dadaan, the Strongest Prone.name: Dadaan, the Strongest Prone
Dadaan, the Strongest Prone.notes: "Dadaan, the Strongest Prone" can be found gracing Mira with his magnificent physical form over at the Scablands Fortress in south west Oblivia. He is protected by the Dadaan Girls who will taunt party members to pull attention away from Dadaan and he will also enter invincibility periods in order to flex while a zergrush of Dadaan Squad Members will be summoned to fight the party. Easy to beat with a Skell superweapon but a fun challenge on foot.

Ga-uhl, the Precept-Keeper.name: Ga-uhl, the Precept-Keeper
Ga-uhl, the Precept-Keeper.notes: "Ga-uhl, the Precept-Keeper" rarely appears during the night at badr stronghold, the ganglion base in the west part of Badr Basin in west Sylvalum. The spawning seems to be tied to the creatures inside the stronghold so despawn and respawn them by moving far away and after some minutes until Ga-uhl eventually appears. When it does appear it will fly in from the direction of the bridge and come to a stop above the highest tower building. Don't go to meet it near the bridge or it will despawn as it reaches the base.

Nardacyon, the Shadowless.name: Nardacyon, the Shadowless
Nardacyon, the Shadowless.notes: "Nardacyon, the Shadowless" and will appear when Nahum is on the brink of defeat and moves into the second phase of the fight. At that point she will board it and continue the fight as Nardacyon. It has incredible evasion stats and powerful attacks. Breaking the back jets increases its power output.

Yuiro, the Luxuriant.name: Yuiro, the Luxuriant
Yuiro, the Luxuriant.notes: "Yuiro, the Luxuriant" will appear in the lone bush when its fellow Blatta have all been killed on top of a tall column of stone at the north end of Qing Long Glade in Noctilum (just below the twin hammers bridge that has a noticeable gap in it). The Blatta will take several seconds to appear and has a short load/despawn distance so land the Skell and be patient.

Squallo, the Sand-Mirer.name: Squallo, the Sand-Mirer
Squallo, the Sand-Mirer.notes: "Squallo, the Sand-Mirer" appears during the day to the north of Cliffside Camp and Aaroy Plain in Oblivia where it will shoot out of the ground once upon getting close enough for the game to load it and then it will retreat and wait below the suspiciously soft sand in the large open area between two mountains and the big arch stone bridge to the north. It will launch a surprise attack on any who wander too close to the centre of the soft sand.

Ilithios, the Enlightened.name: Ilithios, the Enlightened
Ilithios, the Enlightened.notes: "Ilithios, the Enlightened" can be found meditating in the middle of Sunset Falls in Cauldros.

Raider Pugilith.name: Raider Pugilith
Raider Pugilith.notes: "Raider Pugilith" runs up and down a narrow canyon a little ways south of Oblivia Ingress in the west of Oblivia.

Asana, the Azura Star.name: Asana, the Azura Star
Asana, the Azura Star.notes: "Asana, the Azura Star" can be found getting its hoofs wet in the shallow waters of Lake Ciel in Sylvalum. It's towards the southern side of the lake and a little to the west. Alternatively find the base camp in Hilal Meadow and go north.

Tormenta, the Scarlet-Clad.name: Tormenta, the Scarlet-Clad
Tormenta, the Scarlet-Clad.notes: "Tormenta, the Scarlet-Clad" resides at a tiny pond connected to one of the streams feeding into the waterfalls to the south of Decapotamon in central Noctilum.

Bartley, the Conflagration.name: Bartley, the Conflagration
Bartley, the Conflagration.notes: "Bartley, the Conflagration" and its two cohorts love to jump up and down in place in the south of Dragonbone Promontory in Cauldros. Uses Virus.

Falchion, the Vibrant.name: Falchion, the Vibrant
Falchion, the Vibrant.notes: "Falchion, the Vibrant" is under a bridge on the east side of Middle Hushflood in Noctilum (the northmost bridge, not the one that connects directly to the middle island). It takes a moment to come up out of the ground.

Truppe, the Ceaseless Dark.name: Truppe, the Ceaseless Dark
Truppe, the Ceaseless Dark.notes: "Truppe, the Ceaseless Dark" makes an appearance during the night at old ceremonial hollow, a cave to the east of Mount M'gando in Cauldros. Once inside the cave follow the wiggly passage and turn south at the first junction, turn west at the next junction and follow this new wiggly passage to the end to find Truppe surrounded by several other tiny Petramand.

Poppy, the Pyromaniac.name: Poppy, the Pyromaniac
Poppy, the Pyromaniac.notes: "Poppy, the Pyromaniac" is a few rooms within the Lethal Ledges cave in east Cauldros (accessible from the first lava pool north of the Nopon Drongo Caravan). Some platforming required.

Andrei, the Cunning.name: Andrei, the Cunning
Andrei, the Cunning.notes: "Andrei, the Cunning" can be found among many other Caro around the base of Delusions North Summit in Sylvalum.

Lask, the Unscrupulous.name: Lask, the Unscrupulous
Lask, the Unscrupulous.notes: "Lask, the Unscrupulous" is a large Prankster Mephite sleeping under the bridge that connects the North and South Summits at the top of the Delusions mountain on the east side of Sylvalum.

Gugli, the Relentless.name: Gugli, the Relentless
Gugli, the Relentless.notes: "Gugli, the Relentless" can be found on the shore at the north end of Janpath Lake in east Primordia.

Baabara, the Evangelical.name: Baabara, the Evangelical
Baabara, the Evangelical.notes: "Baabara, the Evangelical" can be found grazing during the day among several other sheep-like Ovis to the south east of Janpath Lake in Primorida. Specifically the Ovis are directly east of the basecamp south of Janpath Lake. The shelter at the nearby basecamp can be used to change the time of day if needed.

Gi-zho, the Iron Deity.name: Gi-zho, the Iron Deity
Gi-zho, the Iron Deity.notes: "Gi-zho, the Iron Deity" happily waits for visitors inside a stray large floating drilling platform in the south east corner of Cauldros (near the spikey building). Can be fought on foot but flight is required to reach the drilling platform.

Frajeel, the Purgatorial.name: Frajeel, the Purgatorial
Frajeel, the Purgatorial.notes: "Frajeel, the Purgatorial" floats around just south of the central plant in the dangerous Divine Roost area at Noctilum.

Bressole, the Fugitive.name: Bressole, the Fugitive
Bressole, the Fugitive.notes: "Bressole, the Fugitive" resides on a tiny island at the bottom right corner of the world map. There is a pair of dangerous Ocean Balaena's on the same small island but Bressole can be fought without aggravating either one if you're careful.

WR512: Urdu.name: WR512: Urdu
WR512: Urdu.notes: "WR512: Urdu" can be found from dawn until midnight with a group of Milsaadi down a side passage towards the back of ganglion antropolis in Cauldros. It is easy to become quickly overwhelmed when thoughtlessly engaging in combat. Complete the Definian Downfall mission to gain access to ganglion antropolis.

Necro, the Cavelord.name: Necro, the Cavelord
Necro, the Cavelord.notes: "Necro, the Cavelord" lives in "the shaft" which true to its name is a shaft accessible from the highest mountain in the middle of Primordia. Flight is required to get up there in order to drop down into the shaft. Elvira, the Talondrake sleeps in the top of the shaft during the day but can easily by gotten by without disturbing its slumber.

Gerhardt, the Lone and Proud.name: Gerhardt, the Lone and Proud
Gerhardt, the Lone and Proud.notes: "Gerhardt, the Lone and Proud" resides in Whale's Nostril, a tunnel in the south of Noctilum. It may take some seconds but Gerhardt will drop down out of thin air under a short bridge in the cave while passing by underneath (it attempts to block in BLADE operatives after they check the nearby vehicle wreckage).

Behemoth, the Netherdweller.name: Behemoth, the Netherdweller
Behemoth, the Netherdweller.notes: "Behemoth, the Netherdweller" rarely appears at the very bottom of the Cavernous Abyss, a tall hollow mountain on the western side of Sylvalum. If the regular Virago crawls out of the ground refresh the area until Behemoth appears instead.

Luxaar's Xern.name: Luxaar's Xern
Luxaar's Xern.notes: "Luxaar's Xern" is a giant tripod floating in the sky in the north of Sylvalum. Look up and it is easy to spot.

Giraffin, the Old Hand.name: Giraffin, the Old Hand
Giraffin, the Old Hand.notes: "Giraffin, the Old Hand" is a long legged Lepyx tyrant close to FN Site 413.

Zorn, the Wanderer.name: Zorn, the Wanderer
Zorn, the Wanderer.notes: "Zorn, the Wanderer" appears only during a rainbow in the suspicious room in Old Ceremonial Hollow, a cave accessed from the east side of Mount M'gando in Cauldros. Once inside take a right at the first junction followed by the next possible left to reach a room with water and an altar. Rainbows occur for a short period after rainy weather, brimstone rain included.

Schneider, the Cliffpercher.name: Schneider, the Cliffpercher
Schneider, the Cliffpercher.notes: "Schneider, the Cliffpercher" can be discovered sitting on a perch just over the edge of the lowest level of the multi-part waterfall that is Everwhelm Falls directly above the ocean in Noctilum. If you find some tiny level 10 Violet Forfexes at the edge of the waterfall you're just above Schneider.

Armed Engineer Galdr.name: Armed Engineer Galdr
Armed Engineer Galdr.notes: "Armed Engineer Galdr" can be found above the water just a tiny bit east of Far Isle of Tzo'o in the north west of Cauldros.

Demetrio, the Tempestuous.name: Demetrio, the Tempestuous
Demetrio, the Tempestuous.notes: "Demetrio, the Tempestuous" is in the middle of Ensconced Citadel, a Ganglion outpost up in the mountains north of Qing Long Glade in Noctilum.

Daril, the Eradicator.name: Daril, the Eradicator
Daril, the Eradicator.notes: "Daril, the Eradicator" appears with two other Marnuck during the night at the toxic pool to the north of Arendt Bridge in the northern tip of Primordia.

Diogenes, the Covetous.name: Diogenes, the Covetous
Diogenes, the Covetous.notes: "Diogenes, the Covetous" runs up and down an open passage to the south of Central Ibra Ravine in the east of Oblivia.

Du-rha, the Imprisoned.name: Du-rha, the Imprisoned
Du-rha, the Imprisoned.notes: "Du-rha, the Imprisoned" lies dormant in Quay Hollows cave which can be found in the chunky mountain at the south east of Sylvalum (entrance is on the ocean side).

Uluora, the Burgeoning.name: Uluora, the Burgeoning
Uluora, the Burgeoning.notes: "Uluora, the Burgeoning" can be found up on the mountain ridge that divides White Phosphor Lake from Emerian Battlegrounds in the west side of Cauldros.

Langul, the Alien Payload.name: Langul, the Alien Payload
Langul, the Alien Payload.notes: "Langul, the Alien Payload" stands on the rooftop of a short building in seaswept base in the south east corner of Primordia. Languls building is the on the ridge just to the south of FN Site 119's probe light.

Vittorio, the Battle-Scarred.name: Vittorio, the Battle-Scarred
Vittorio, the Battle-Scarred.notes: "Vittorio, the Battle-Scarred" is a rocky turtle like creature hiding in the floor close to the mountain northwest of Bardarich Desert in Oblivia with just the top of its shell sticking out. Easily mistaken for part of the scenery.

Olegario, the Iron-Helmed.name: Olegario, the Iron-Helmed
Olegario, the Iron-Helmed.notes: "Olegario, the Iron-Helmed" appears during the night at the hidden spring "whale's weeper" in the southern part of Noctilum. Whale's weeper can be entered from a small side path at waterway tangle just to the east of Old Dragontail Tree.

Lockhart, the Killer of Hope.name: Lockhart, the Killer of Hope
Lockhart, the Killer of Hope.notes: "Lockhart, the Killer of Hope" rarely appears near at the base of the tree that holds up the gigantic sphere in the south west of Sylvalum.

Latis, the Bristle-Scaled.name: Latis, the Bristle-Scaled
Latis, the Bristle-Scaled.notes: "Latis, the Bristle-Scaled" rarely appears in a pond next to FN Site 418 in northern Sylvalum. Refresh until it spawns instead of one of the Cerulean Arenatects.

Roimi, the Affluent.name: Roimi, the Affluent
Roimi, the Affluent.notes: "Roimi, the Affluent" can be spotted at night way up a god damned tree on the rocky rocks in the south west corner of Janpath Lake in Primordia. Roimi is a golden blatta that may take a moment to load in after every thing else in the area has loaded. If you're still having trouble look for the rocks with the most trees that Luciel walks around to drink at either side.

Rajidi, the Cumuliform.name: Rajidi, the Cumuliform
Rajidi, the Cumuliform.notes: "Rajidi, the Cumuliform" rarely appears just to the south of the connecting bridge to Oblivia in the far eastern edge of Primordia.

Elena, the Infernal.name: Elena, the Infernal
Elena, the Infernal.notes: "Elena, the Infernal" appears during dense fog at Weeping Whitewood in Noctilum.

Sven, the Sturdy.name: Sven, the Sturdy
Sven, the Sturdy.notes: "Sven, the Sturdy" is on what I dub to be crab island out in the ocean to the west of Primordia (south of Noctilum). Sven is indeed very sturdy and reduces all incoming attacks to just 1 point of damage thanks to having Attribute Resistances of 100 for every element. Moves that reduce/ignore resistances will tear through those defences (e.g. Ares super weapon, Blossom Dance Art, etc). A Mech 5 treasure on the same island contains FILE-USP0460ME, the level 50 Trident-Anchor Skell weapon schematic.

Eutropio, the Sea Rumble.name: Eutropio, the Sea Rumble
Eutropio, the Sea Rumble.notes: "Eutropio, the Sea Rumble" flies around underneath the roofed area south of Janpath Lake in east Primordia.

Rodriguez, the Twin-Tusked.name: Rodriguez, the Twin-Tusked
Rodriguez, the Twin-Tusked.notes: "Rodriguez, the Twin-Tusked" can be found in the north eastern part of the Emerian Battlegrounds in Cauldros.

Damaged Zig.name: Damaged Zig
Damaged Zig.notes: "Damaged Zig" faces the southern ocean on a piece of rib like mountain sticking out over the water at the south west cliff surrounding the hilal stronghold ganglion base in Hilal Meadow in Sylvalum.

Experimental Composite Qmoeva.name: Experimental Composite Qmoeva
Experimental Composite Qmoeva.notes: "Experimental Composite Qmoeva" can be found at night at talon rock summit atop the highest mountain in central Primordia (in the segment directly north of FN Site 110). Flight is required for at least the initial trip to the top of the mountain.

Shatskikh, the Flash.name: Shatskikh, the Flash
Shatskikh, the Flash.notes: "Shatskikh, the Flash" rarely appears at Northpointe Cove in Primordia. A trick to get rare Tyrants to appear is to move far enough away that the indigens disappear and then move back in closer to make the game load them again and repeat until it decides to load Shatskihk instead of a regular Sea Xiphias.

Xair, the Cerulean Walker.name: Xair, the Cerulean Walker
Xair, the Cerulean Walker.notes: "Xair, the Cerulean Walker" resides on a remote island in the ocean to the south west of Sylvalum. Deals heavy spike damage but can simply be OHKO with some Theroid Slayer XX augments and a super weapon.

Ernest, the Comptemplative.name: Ernest, the Comptemplative
Ernest, the Comptemplative.notes: "Ernest, the Comptemplative" rests near the mountain wall a little to the west of the bottom of King's Falls in Oblivia.

Ahama, the Covetous.name: Ahama, the Covetous
Ahama, the Covetous.notes: "Ahama, the Covetous" appears in the same spot during the night.

Chantai, the Insect Maiden.name: Chantai, the Insect Maiden
Chantai, the Insect Maiden.notes: "Chantai, the Insect Maiden" can be found at night in the saucer high above Abandoned Bivouac in the north of Cauldros.

Lyla's Galdr.name: Lyla's Galdr
Lyla's Galdr.notes: "Lyla's Galdr" is a rare spawn that can sometimes take the place of a Green Lance Galdr that lands at the large rock shelf controlled by Ganglion forces near Hardheart Canyon to the north east of Lake Ciel in Sylvalum. Both the tyrant and non-tyrant Galdr only appear for the short period between 5am and 7am and have the same pattern. Stay near the middle of the three lights on the shelf and look south to see the Galdr fly in. If it's the Green Lance Galdr fly to the north until it fades out and return to the light to have the game reload the Galdr for another chance to spawn Lyla's Galdr. Use the nearby base camp to change time.

Vilem, the Gold-Scaled.name: Vilem, the Gold-Scaled
Vilem, the Gold-Scaled.notes: "Vilem, the Gold-Scaled" pops out of the water at the south east corner of Lake Basil in Oblvia.

Stola, the Unchained.name: Stola, the Unchained
Stola, the Unchained.notes: "Stola, the Unchained" appears during rising energy mists to take part in a freaky trumpet bird courtship ritual in the eastern side of the top of the Delusions South Summit. Drops a special Longsword with low attack but high TP gain.

Florence, the Hell Maggot.name: Florence, the Hell Maggot
Florence, the Hell Maggot.notes: "Florence, the Hell Maggot" pretends to be larger than normal beautiful blossoming nocturnal plant close to the cliff wall in the south west of Hilal Meadow in Sylvalum. It won't attack Skells and as an ambush predator it cannot be targetted until it makes the first move so start the battle on foot.

Jarosch, the Sensational.name: Jarosch, the Sensational
Jarosch, the Sensational.notes: "Jarosch, the Sensational" very rarely spawns in place of a Jade Saltat on the large and very noticeable bunch of red/pink flowers growing on the large arching tree in the middle of Rustpool Bank. The spawning distance is so short that you have to land directly on the flower and then wait for several seconds before the game loads the Jade Saltat/Jarosch into the world. Instead of reloading the entire area with fast travel/return to Skell it will be faster to fly straight up until the Jade Saltat despawns and then drop down so the game loads it into the gameworld again and rerolls the dice on which creature is loaded.

Support Trainee Qmoeva.name: Support Trainee Qmoeva
Support Trainee Qmoeva.notes: "Support Trainee Qmoeva" can be found at night stationed on a tall tower towards the south end of seaswept base in the south east corner of Primordia. Approach it to wake it up.

Si-el, the Vacuous.name: Si-el, the Vacuous
Si-el, the Vacuous.notes: "Si-el, the Vacuous" is an Oc-serv laying dormant on the floor in Qing Long Glade in the central area of Noctilum (just south from the Qing Long Glade basecamp). Dormant Oc-servs will typically only awaken to attack Skells but by using area of effect attacks on nearby targets which then indirectly damage the sleepy Oc-servs they can be drawn into combat while on foot.

Candelario, the Bronze.name: Candelario, the Bronze
Candelario, the Bronze.notes: "Candelario, the Bronze" can be found on a small bump north of Baldr Basin in the north west of Sylvalum.

High-Output Pugilith.name: High-Output Pugilith
High-Output Pugilith.notes: "High-Output Pugilith" patrols the entry ramp that leads down into the Ganglion base in the west part of Baldr Basin.

Shinhwa, the Sagacious.name: Shinhwa, the Sagacious
Shinhwa, the Sagacious.notes: "Shinhwa, the Sagacious" rests on a small island in the middle of the lake just north of Decapotamon in central Noctilum.

Eustachio, the Eccentric.name: Eustachio, the Eccentric
Eustachio, the Eccentric.notes: "Eustachio, the Eccentric" stealthily poses during the night just outside the entrance to behemoth's shadows, an expansive cavern accessible above Sylvalum Searoad to the east of Sylvalum (at FN Site 420).

Ludvik, the Picky Eater.name: Ludvik, the Picky Eater
Ludvik, the Picky Eater.notes: "Ludvik, the Picky Eater" appears during the day in the centre of Keegans Ridge in Oblivia.

Elvira, the Talondrake.name: Elvira, the Talondrake
Elvira, the Talondrake.notes: "Elvira, the Talondrake" lives on the highest mountain in Primordia, accessible only by flight. During the day it sleeps in The Shaft and at night it can be found flying around it's high home.

Bogdan, the Dense.name: Bogdan, the Dense
Bogdan, the Dense.notes: "Bogdan, the Dense" is at seaswept base in the south east corner of Primordia. It is just across the bridge from the building where you first meet Tatsu.

Rolf, the Sonorous.name: Rolf, the Sonorous
Rolf, the Sonorous.notes: "Rolf, the Sonorous" can be found near the bottom of Kings Falls in Oblivia dancing on the sand.

Zdenka, the Raucous.name: Zdenka, the Raucous
Zdenka, the Raucous.notes: "Zdenka, the Raucous" sits atop a tall stone pillar at fallshom isle, the stoney home of some level 50 Saltats to the north west of Grieving Plains in western Primordia. Zdenka can take ten or more seconds to load when reaching this area. Flight not necessary but be prepared for a ranged battle.

Sarcosuchus, the Iron-Eater.name: Sarcosuchus, the Iron-Eater
Sarcosuchus, the Iron-Eater.notes: "Sarcosuchus, the Iron-Eater" will leap out and surprise anyone who enters the deep part of the pool directly between three Dilus (crocodiles) in the north part of Rust Lake in Noctilums southern half.

Yelena, the Sequestered.name: Yelena, the Sequestered
Yelena, the Sequestered.notes: "Yelena, the Sequestered" can be found in the shadows of the large rock just to the east of Janpath Lake in eastern Primordia.

Daemon, the Undertaker.name: Daemon, the Undertaker
Daemon, the Undertaker.notes: "Daemon, the Undertaker" can be found inside of the Den of the Dead cave underneath Delusions North Summit in Sylvalum. The cave entrance is at ground floor at FN Site 416. From the entrance take two rights to find Daemon.

Calore, the Lava Walker.name: Calore, the Lava Walker
Calore, the Lava Walker.notes: "Calore, the Lava Walker" can be found in the first pocket of lava south of White Phosphor Lake in Cauldros (between Drongo Caravan and Emerian Battlegrounds).

Experimental Compact Zig.name: Experimental Compact Zig
Experimental Compact Zig.notes: "Experimental Compact Zig" is up on the cliff west of Scholes Battlegrounds in Cauldros.

Joker, the Unknowable.name: Joker, the Unknowable
Joker, the Unknowable.notes: "Joker, the Unknowable" is inside the top of the giant plant at Divine Roost at the northern tip of Noctilum along with 19 level 60 Blatta friends. They are a great source for quickly levelling up party members, levelling Classes and stocking up on Tatty Insect Wings to create Insectoid Slayer Augments.

Lugalbanda, the Wanderer-King.name: Lugalbanda, the Wanderer-King
Lugalbanda, the Wanderer-King.notes: "Lugalbanda, the Wanderer-King" lives in a secret side passage within vitriol cesspool, a cave trying to live up to its name in a literal sense that is located south of Serpentines Pass in Noctilum (alternatively fast travel to FN Site 209 and follow the foul water into the cave). Once inside the cave head into the water and swim through a small crack on the leftside (southside) of the caves main room, at the end of the long tunnels through this crack stands Lugalbanda.

Lyla, the Lustrous.name: Lyla, the Lustrous
Lyla, the Lustrous.notes: "Lyla, the Lustrous" guards the archaeological treasure in the south west corner of the largest room in the Den of the Dead cave in Sylvalum and will ambush those who go near it.

Logistical Support Quo.name: Logistical Support Quo
Logistical Support Quo.notes: "Logistical Support Quo" sits on a spherical light near the lone tower in the back of bedrock hold, the Ganglion base located in the far north west corner of Primordia.

Armed Recon Galdr.name: Armed Recon Galdr
Armed Recon Galdr.notes: "Armed Recon Galdr" is on a sandy island way out in the ocean to the south west of Cauldros. It rests in its transformed ship state until enemies get close. There is an archaeological 4 treasure on the island rewarding an Auto Attack Cooldown XX augment (20% faster auto attacks).

Yama, the Obliviator.name: Yama, the Obliviator
Yama, the Obliviator.notes: "Yama, the Obliviator" obliterates any travellers who get too close. It loiters at the south end of the Elephants Trunk bridge in south Noctilm.

Roderick, the Fleet-Footed.name: Roderick, the Fleet-Footed
Roderick, the Fleet-Footed.notes: "Roderick, the Fleet-Footed" runs between two points during the day in the East Gate Plain in Primordia. Each point is on the opposite of the dirt road leading away from NLA with the first one being a little north west of the beach at East Gate Plain on the north side of the road and the second point is just north of the same beach but on the south side of the road.

Vendura's Galdr.name: Vendura's Galdr
Vendura's Galdr.notes: "Vendura's Galdr" stands guard at night in the Scablands Fortress in Oblivia.

Albin, the Wicked Meddler.name: Albin, the Wicked Meddler
Albin, the Wicked Meddler.notes: "Albin, the Wicked Meddler" can be found during the night floating around the western side of Lake Ciel. It spawns on top of Laurencio, the Fog Bow and then goes for a wander.

Nu-rhor, the Dark Deity.name: Nu-rhor, the Dark Deity
Nu-rhor, the Dark Deity.notes: "Nu-rhor, the Dark Deity" stands guard in the Ganglion fortress to the south east of Sea Whisper Valley in east Oblivia.

Sharnaak's Seidr.name: Sharnaak's Seidr
Sharnaak's Seidr.notes: "Sharnaak's Seidr" resides inside ganglion antroplois, a cave that is blocked off until the Definian Downfall mission unlocks the energy barrier preventing access. Ganglion Antropolis is accessed from a cave near the lava at the south west edge of Ruined City of O'rrh Sim

Tico, the Precious.name: Tico, the Precious
Tico, the Precious.notes: "Tico, the Precious" can be found in one of the very short tunnels within beehive rock, a donut like rocky area up in the mountains above Central Ibra Ravine in Oblivia. Flight though not 100% required is highly advised.

Laurencio, the Fog Bow.name: Laurencio, the Fog Bow
Laurencio, the Fog Bow.notes: "Laurencio, the Fog Bow" is a super massive plant in the eastern half of Lake Ciel, getting close enough to touch it will start the fight. A tough opponent without a super weapon.

Kringe, the Hunting Arrow.name: Kringe, the Hunting Arrow
Kringe, the Hunting Arrow.notes: "Kringe, the Hunting Arrow" appears on the bridge to the west of Titans Table.

Andrea, the Famished Hunter.name: Andrea, the Famished Hunter
Andrea, the Famished Hunter.notes: "Andrea, the Famished Hunter" roams the western shore of Sylvalums Lake Ciel with a pack of Villainous Caucus in tow.

Seti, the Light of Stars.name: Seti, the Light of Stars
Seti, the Light of Stars.notes: "Seti, the Light of Stars" appears during the night at the hidden spring "whale's weeper" in the southern part of Noctilum. Whale's weeper can be entered from a small side path at waterway tangle just to the east of Old Dragontail Tree.

Camus, the Treasured.name: Camus, the Treasured
Camus, the Treasured.notes: "Camus, the Treasured" lives inside a small tunnel at the back end of Beastial Utopia, a cave which can be entered from the north base of Mount M'gando in north east Cauldros.

Mesgen, the Fairweathered.name: Mesgen, the Fairweathered
Mesgen, the Fairweathered.notes: "Mesgen, the Fairweathered" rests on the shore at the eastern end of Sayram Lake in central Primordia.

Polaris, the Firmamental.name: Polaris, the Firmamental
Polaris, the Firmamental.notes: "Polaris, the Firmamental" can be found during the night above the spiky building near Ruined City of O'rrh Sim in northern Cauldros.

Eddy, the Electric Heat.name: Eddy, the Electric Heat
Eddy, the Electric Heat.notes: "Eddy, the Electric Heat" swims close to the lava underneath the rocky arch that holds up Titans Table in west Cauldros.

Ji-ett, the Thunderclap.name: Ji-ett, the Thunderclap
Ji-ett, the Thunderclap.notes: "Ji-ett, the Thunderclap" will appear at night high in the sky at the south east corner of Primordia. It is in the segment south of FN Site 120 above the tip of the tall, thin mountain.

Prototype Puge.name: Prototype Puge
Prototype Puge.notes: "Prototype Puge" can be found upstairs in a building at bedrock hold, the ganglion base in the north west corner of Primordia. As you approach the bases outer walls on foot take a right where the dirt path splits. The building with Prototype Puge is the two floor one just inside the front of the base. Don't forget you can open the doors.

Badul's Seidr.name: Badul's Seidr
Badul's Seidr.notes: "Badul's Seidr" appears at the same spot during the day.

Shuravas, the Enraged.name: Shuravas, the Enraged
Shuravas, the Enraged.notes: "Shuravas, the Enraged" appears during thunderstorms to fly through the canyon north of Qing Long Glade in central Noctilum. Breaking the fin is the only way to recieve the "Signature Glaive: Allegiance" drop however breaking the fin also causes it to enrage making the remainder of the fight more difficult.

Dawid, the Destrier.name: Dawid, the Destrier
Dawid, the Destrier.notes: "Dawid, the Destrier" can be found up on the mountain that divides White Phosphor Lake and Emerian Battlegrounds in the west side of Cauldros.

Enhanced Attack Range Zig.name: Enhanced Attack Range Zig
Enhanced Attack Range Zig.notes: "Enhanced Attack Range Zig" defends the interior of the O'rrh Sim Castle Ruins at Cauldros. From the O'rrh Sim Gate enter the larger of the two entrances (assuming you've already opened it during the story) and then turn to the left in this larger room to see a smaller passage which leads to another large room containing the Zig.

Telethia, the Endbringer.name: Telethia, the Endbringer
Telethia, the Endbringer.notes: "Telethia, the Endbringer" circles above the entire Divine Roost area in the far northern tip of Noctilum.

Gradivus, the Headless Emperor.name: Gradivus, the Headless Emperor
Gradivus, the Headless Emperor.notes: "Gradivus, the Headless Emperor" is a post game boss that appears at Oblivia's North Coast after completing the story. Supposedly has just over one hundred million HP.

Edgardo, the Carefree.name: Edgardo, the Carefree
Edgardo, the Carefree.notes: "Edgardo, the Carefree" cleverly pretends to be simple tree branches clinging to a stone tower at Oblivias North Coast area and strikes when prey comes too close.

Luciel, the Eternal.name: Luciel, the Eternal
Luciel, the Eternal.notes: "Luciel, the Eternal" drinks from Janpath Lake in east Primordia. It can keep its foes toppled while trampling them to death.

Camille, the Immortal.name: Camille, the Immortal
Camille, the Immortal.notes: "Camille, the Immortal" flutters back and forth in the centre of the pond at Cleansing Spring in Sylvaum.

Zohan, the thunderbolt.name: Zohan, the thunderbolt
Zohan, the thunderbolt.notes: "Zohan, the thunderbolt" appears during spores, the blinding weather unique to Sylvalum. It appears above Delusians North Summit at the top of the gigantic blossomed spike plant (quite high in the air). Simply land on the plant, step out of the Skell and use the Return to Skell menu option to refresh the game world in order to quickly cycle through weather states until Spores appear and then fly straight up to meet Zohan (can also land directly on the top spike with some care).

Clara, the Pure White.name: Clara, the Pure White
Clara, the Pure White.notes: "Clara, the Pure White" can be found grazing during the day in a field of cotton flowers around other Ovis and some Lepyx directly to the south of Cauldros Threshold in the northern tip of Sylvalum. Attacking her will provoke all surrounding Ovis.

Ridill, the Arrogant.name: Ridill, the Arrogant
Ridill, the Arrogant.notes: "Ridill, the Arrogant" rarely appears in Primordia's northern waters directly north of FN Site 109. Fast travel to probe 109 to reload the area after checking the pair of Ocean Lophids that spawn just to the north until Ridill appears. Bit of a damage sponge.

Prinsipe, the Ravenous.name: Prinsipe, the Ravenous
Prinsipe, the Ravenous.notes: "Prinsipe, the Ravenous" can be found at night on the ancient drilling platform to the north west of Slavebird Isle in Cauldros.

Enhanced Defense Seidr.name: Enhanced Defense Seidr
Enhanced Defense Seidr.notes: "Enhanced Defense Seidr" sits between the tripod legs of Luxaar's Xern above Anvil Sandplain in northern Sylvalum.

Oc-serv, the Ancient.name: Oc-serv, the Ancient
Oc-serv, the Ancient.notes: "Oc-serv, the Ancient" lies dormant waiting to ambush a Skell south of Sylvalum Searoad in the east of Sylvalum. Either approach it in a Skell or lure over a nearby Villainous Caecus and use an Area of Effect attack to start the fight.

Ramus, the Supersonic.name: Ramus, the Supersonic
Ramus, the Supersonic.notes: "Ramus, the Supersonic" flies in one of groups of Aetrygon above the north east corner of Lake Ciel. Specifically in the group that flies near the level 60 Assault Launcher Zig that lies at the end of a deliberate footpath that climbs the small mountain that borders the north of Lake Ciel in Sylvalum.

Nahum, the Red Hare.name: Nahum, the Red Hare
Nahum, the Red Hare.notes: "Nahum, the Red Hare" and continues the fight aboard her Skell. She becomes invincible when her HP is very low. She can use mind control.

Balduino, the Wicked-Eyed.name: Balduino, the Wicked-Eyed
Balduino, the Wicked-Eyed.notes: "Balduino, the Wicked-Eyed" lives up on the small cliff in the north east part of Divine Roost in Noctilum among many other Aeviters who wait patiently to ambush prey. Balduino is the Aeviter that is closest to the treasure. The crashed chopper it guards requires contains an EZ Debuff Probe (requires Mechanical 4 to salvage).

Gesserith, the Wileworm.name: Gesserith, the Wileworm
Gesserith, the Wileworm.notes: "Gesserith, the Wileworm" may be summoned into battle by her mate, Atreides, when he is at low health. Gesserith will immediately inflict taunt to force the party to attack her in an effort to protect Atreides.

Draken, the Drifting Cloud.name: Draken, the Drifting Cloud
Draken, the Drifting Cloud.notes: "Draken, the Drifting Cloud" floats around in the tropical areas out in the Primordia Waters between Primordia and Sylvalum. Starts high above the small mountain on the largest tropical island and descends from there. Has two smaller Balaena on either side. Big enough to be mistaken for the shadow of a cloud.

Pyotr, the Shepherd.name: Pyotr, the Shepherd
Pyotr, the Shepherd.notes: "Pyotr, the Shepherd" is at the grassy area north west of Middle Hushflood in Noctilum. True to its name Pyotr is a shepherd of two Ovis and will enrage if you kill the herd first.

Radovan, the Sky Baron.name: Radovan, the Sky Baron
Radovan, the Sky Baron.notes: "Radovan, the Sky Baron" can be found during the day landing and resting upon the tallest piece of rib like mountain that extends over the north west corner of Lake Ciel (just before the arches)

Agnes, the Divine-Scaled.name: Agnes, the Divine-Scaled
Agnes, the Divine-Scaled.notes: "Agnes, the Divine-Scaled" can be found around a heavy concentration of rocks in the lava between Titan's Table and Dragonebone Promontory in Cauldros.

Antara, the Water Diviner.name: Antara, the Water Diviner
Antara, the Water Diviner.notes: "Antara, the Water Diviner" sits partially buried in the ground alongside some similar but real rocks north west of Anvil Sandplain in the north of Sylvalum (close to FN Site 407).

Stola, the Champion.name: Stola, the Champion
Stola, the Champion.notes: "Stola, the Champion" will appear at the south east tip of Seabirds Beak in Sylvalum during a Crimson Aurora.

Eckart, the Indestructible.name: Eckart, the Indestructible
Eckart, the Indestructible.notes: "Eckart, the Indestructible" will borrow up out of the ground on the raised platform to the east of Grieving Plains in Primordia.

Germaine, the Treasure Keeper.name: Germaine, the Treasure Keeper
Germaine, the Treasure Keeper.notes: "Germaine, the Treasure Keeper" rests in a small hollow section of the mountain north of the Yawning Giant in Oblivia. Requires a Skell to either fly in or leap up to the overhanging ledge above the Twin Arches.

Hartmut, the Calamity.name: Hartmut, the Calamity
Hartmut, the Calamity.notes: "Hartmut, the Calamity" is the big thing that flies around much of Yawning Giant, the bottomless ravine in Oblivia (starts in the south)

Sirene, the Lost.name: Sirene, the Lost
Sirene, the Lost.notes: "Sirene, the Lost" is a long legged Lepyx that can be found halfway between East Gate Plain and Sickle Rock Rise in east Primordia (near FN Site 114).

Feliciano, the All-Seeing.name: Feliciano, the All-Seeing
Feliciano, the All-Seeing.notes: "Feliciano, the All-Seeing" appears during the day in the open space north of Central Ibra Ravine in east Oblivia. Seems to have some sort of powerful spike damage effect that injures attackers.

Lomoth, the Beast-Eater.name: Lomoth, the Beast-Eater
Lomoth, the Beast-Eater.notes: "Lomoth, the Beast-Eater" can be found up on the mountains to the east of Central Ibra Ravine in east Oblivia in a field of flowers near some strange trumpet birds. As a Germivore it is hiding in the ground with it's flower like butt sticking out.

Leandro, the Sneering.name: Leandro, the Sneering
Leandro, the Sneering.notes: "Leandro, the Sneering" is one of several tyrants that reside within behemoth's shadows, an expansive cavern accessible above Sylvalum Searoad to the east of Sylvalum (at FN Site 420).

Heidi, the Lively.name: Heidi, the Lively
Heidi, the Lively.notes: "Heidi, the Lively" can be found at the grassy area north west of Middle Hushflood in Noctilum and is the second half of the pair of Ovis that Pyotr, the Shepherd guards. Heidi can cast Sleep on your entire party.

Eisen, the Ebon Rock.name: Eisen, the Ebon Rock
Eisen, the Ebon Rock.notes: "Eisen, the Ebon Rock" appears during the night to ambush prey on the largest rock in the middle of the lavafall between Ruined City of O'rrh Sim and Abandoned Bivouac in north Cauldros. It may take Eisen a moment to appear once you are on the rock. During the day a different Petramand Tyrant appears in the lava nearby.

Planetes, the Torrential.name: Planetes, the Torrential
Planetes, the Torrential.notes: "Planetes, the Torrential" is above the waterfall at Divine Roost in the north of Noctilum. Fly up to the top of the waterfall and then continue flying further up to find it.

Yune, the Ambusher.name: Yune, the Ambusher
Yune, the Ambusher.notes: "Yune, the Ambusher" is a rare spawn at the north west shore of Seabirds Beak which is the beach at the south end of Sylvalum that sticks out into the ocean. Either reload the area with fast travel/return to Skell or move in and out of the spawn area until the game loads Yune.

Infantry Support Qmoeva.name: Infantry Support Qmoeva
Infantry Support Qmoeva.notes: "Infantry Support Qmoeva" resides in the top left of the WORLD map near the invisible walls of the game world (consider using R+B to activate auto run and admire the ocean and sky views as you travel all the way out there. It has near invincibility phases but low HP.

Desdemona, the Subterraanean.name: Desdemona, the Subterraanean
Desdemona, the Subterraanean.notes: "Desdemona, the Subterraanean" can be found up on a large chunk of rock at the west part of Rustpool Bank in the southern section of Noctilum.

Armored Cruiser Seidr.name: Armored Cruiser Seidr
Armored Cruiser Seidr.notes: "Armored Cruiser Seidr" will appear during the day near a large Guide Eagle Galdr that is parked on the top of the outer ring of the ganglion weapons hanger. Specifically the parked Guide Eagle Galdr that is on the southeast quadrant, not the Galdr along the south.

Armed Destroyer Galdr.name: Armed Destroyer Galdr
Armed Destroyer Galdr.notes: "Armed Destroyer Galdr" can be found floating in the Ruined City of O'rrh Sim in the north of Cauldros.

Casper, the Unhealthy Eater.name: Casper, the Unhealthy Eater
Casper, the Unhealthy Eater.notes: "Casper, the Unhealthy Eater" appears during the night just outside of NLA's west gate up in the rocks to the south where it's hidden from view between the rocks at the top of the hill and the crystallised spikes from the crash landing.

Yessenia, the Husky-Voiced.name: Yessenia, the Husky-Voiced
Yessenia, the Husky-Voiced.notes: "Yessenia, the Husky-Voiced" sits in the water south of Humdrum Peaks in Noctilum, mere steps away from from probe FN Site 221. Wake it up and lure it to land when fighting on foot.

Experimental Flight Shrad.name: Experimental Flight Shrad
Experimental Flight Shrad.notes: "Experimental Flight Shrad" will fall out of the sky and land on a ramped walkway in the sky just to the east of Abandoned Bivouac in north Cauldros. It will spawn when you are about a third away from the top of the ramp.

Blaudolch, the Chalcedony.name: Blaudolch, the Chalcedony
Blaudolch, the Chalcedony.notes: "Blaudolch, the Chalcedony" can be found resting at Seabird's Beak in the south of Sylvalum (in the same segment as FN Site 403).

Sadar's Qmoeva.name: Sadar's Qmoeva
Sadar's Qmoeva.notes: "Sadar's Qmoeva" can be found during the day parked on a small rock shelf a little north east of Lake Ciel in Sylvalum.

Egg Blatta.name: Egg Blatta
Egg Blatta.notes: Found at [19:00~5:00]:occasionally replaces Nocto Blatta at Suid corpses

Sapara, the Laconic.name: Sapara, the Laconic
Sapara, the Laconic.notes: "Sapara, the Laconic" can be found close to the river between Stickstone Rise and Unicorn Rock in the north west of Primordia.

Sector Security Shrad.name: Sector Security Shrad
Sector Security Shrad.notes: "Sector Security Shrad" can be seen rolling around in the first half of a nameless Ganglion base that is in the canyon just to the east of T'Phnom Shelf towards the south eastern parts of Cauldros.

Dobromila, the Alluring.name: Dobromila, the Alluring
Dobromila, the Alluring.notes: "Dobromila, the Alluring" is a spinning plant look-a-like waiting to ambush prey in the waters of the western side of Lake Ciel in Sylvalum.

Tourteau, the Delectable.name: Tourteau, the Delectable
Tourteau, the Delectable.notes: "Tourteau, the Delectable" can be found at night on the eastern half of the beach near the East Gate Plains in Primordia.

Gotthard, the Intimidating.name: Gotthard, the Intimidating
Gotthard, the Intimidating.notes: "Gotthard, the Intimidating" flies in quick circles over the northern area of the bottomless abyss that is the Yawning Giant in Oblivia.

Angelita, the Blade Bouquet.name: Angelita, the Blade Bouquet
Angelita, the Blade Bouquet.notes: "Angelita, the Blade Bouquet" rests in the Mount M'gando Mineral Spring hidden at the top of Mount M'gando in Cauldos.

No-dhor, the Shadowcaster.name: No-dhor, the Shadowcaster
No-dhor, the Shadowcaster.notes: "No-dhor, the Shadowcaster" can be found north of Lake Basil in Oblivia. Reflects Gravity damage.

Natt, the Inestimable.name: Natt, the Inestimable
Natt, the Inestimable.notes: "Natt, the Inestimable" rarely makes an appearance in the same interior room as the probe light for FN Site 507 at the top of Slavebird Isle in Cauldros. Besides fast travelling over and over until the game loads Natt instead of the third Hellion Blatta it is also possible to fly back and forth outside at an angle that allows you to see when the Blatta despawn and respawn until the noticeable purple tyrant splotch appears.

Frontline Medic Quo.name: Frontline Medic Quo
Frontline Medic Quo.notes: "Frontline Medic Quo" defends the interior of the O'rrh Sim Castle Ruins at Cauldros. It will ambush the party in the middle of the highest floor of the rooms that overlook the ganglion weapons hanger. From the O'rrh Sim Gate simply enter the smaller of the two entrances to the interior and it will lead to the Quo tyrant.

Froste, the Courteous.name: Froste, the Courteous
Froste, the Courteous.notes: "Froste, the Courteous" can be found at the back of vitriol cesspool, a cave at FN Site 209 in the west of central Noctilum. It is past the falsaxum, not in the hidden side passage.

Ignit, the Ultimate Chaos.name: Ignit, the Ultimate Chaos
Ignit, the Ultimate Chaos.notes: "Ignit, the Ultimate Chaos" will appear in the eastern half of Lake Ciel in Sylvalum during a Crimson Aurora. During the Crimson Aurora the normally docile Ancient Coronid in the area will become aggressive Frenzied Coronid.

Ald, the Extravagant.name: Ald, the Extravagant
Ald, the Extravagant.notes: "Ald, the Extravagant" is hiding in Quay Hollows in the south east of Sylvalum (accessed via the ocean side of the mountain near the giant sphere). It is in the same room as Du-rha, the Imprisoned in the north west corner behind a pillar on a high platform with an Archeological treasure.

Berserker Marnuck.name: Berserker Marnuck
Berserker Marnuck.notes: "Berserker Marnuck" defends the steps to the O'rrh Sim Gate in the western section of O'rrh Sim Castle Ruins in Cauldros. He fights alongside a small squad of Marnucks and a pair of Zigs that will all immediately join any fight he partakes in.

Trueno, the Cataclysm.name: Trueno, the Cataclysm
Trueno, the Cataclysm.notes: "Trueno, the Cataclysm" is a super massive Filiavent residing in White Phosphor Lake. One would normally avoid such an imposing enemy however it has the unfortunate luck of sitting right on top of a teleporter that is the only entrance to a nearby floating platform containing the one of a kind "Reflect: Ether" augment (only other source for this augment in the game is a level 99 Tyrant who also happens to use a lot of Ether attacks).

Urdu's Qmoeva.name: Urdu's Qmoeva
Urdu's Qmoeva.notes: "Urdu's Qmoeva" is active for just a very short time from midnight until dawn in ganglion antropolis in Cauldros. To find it enter ganglion antropolis under FN Site 505, head over the arched bridge with the marnucks and puglith and turn right to find more marnucks and Urdu's Qmoeva. Complete the Definian Downfall mission to gain access to ganglion antropolis.

Daril's Qmoeva.name: Daril's Qmoeva
Daril's Qmoeva.notes: "Daril's Qmoeva" can found during the day investigating starfall basin, the area where you first woke up on Mira, in the southwest corner of Primordia.

Badul, the One-Eyed.name: Badul, the One-Eyed
Badul, the One-Eyed.notes: "Badul, the One-Eyed" is a hoodless daytime assassin that will drop out of no where to surprise visitors on the rooftop of a building in the south west corner of hilal stronghold, the Ganglion base to the south of Hilal Meadow in sourthern Sylvalum. The door to the roof is locked but a nearby raised path makes it easy to simply jump onto the roof on foot.

Terenty, the Blademaster.name: Terenty, the Blademaster
Terenty, the Blademaster.notes: "Terenty, the Blademaster" can be found down the side of a building on the southern side of Mount M'gando in Cauldros. Where the southern path that leads up to Mount M'gando has a U-bend with a dormant Xe-dom is a western wall that can be climbed over to find Terenty in the ditch on the otherside.

Valyrion, the Iron Cleaver.name: Valyrion, the Iron Cleaver
Valyrion, the Iron Cleaver.notes: "Valyrion, the Iron Cleaver" drops out of the sky to ambush travellers at the bend of the path next to Kings Falls leading to the empty base.

Durvin, the Perceptive.name: Durvin, the Perceptive
Durvin, the Perceptive.notes: "Durvin, the Perceptive" appears during the day inside of beasts lair, a Grex filled cave that can be entered from the northern edge of Sayram Lake in central Primordia.

Alfombra, the Transcendent.name: Alfombra, the Transcendent
Alfombra, the Transcendent.notes: "Alfombra, the Transcendent" is a cheeky rock turtle kind of thing hiding in the ground and waiting for travellers passing through Humdrum Peaks in southern Noctilum.

Night Combat Puge.name: Night Combat Puge
Night Combat Puge.notes: "Night Combat Puge" appears during the night on a walkway connected to the large spiky building in the north west of Cauldros.

Dieter, the Epicure.name: Dieter, the Epicure
Dieter, the Epicure.notes: "Dieter, the Epicure" is a Grex that appears above beasts lair at the north side of Sayram Lake in central Primordia.

Ro-darm, the Demon Claw.name: Ro-darm, the Demon Claw
Ro-darm, the Demon Claw.notes: "Ro-darm, the Demon Claw" can be found at North Coast in Oblivia laying in a heap on the floor near the walls of the mountain along the eastern side. As with other dormant types of Oc-serv it will typically only wake up to ambush Skells.

Piernus, the Scorcher.name: Piernus, the Scorcher
Piernus, the Scorcher.notes: "Piernus, the Scorcher" appears during the day in the middle of the lava between Ruined City of O'rrh Sim and Abandoned Bivouac in north Cauldros. During the night a different Petramand Tyrant appears on a rock nearby.

Izgnanie, the Smoldering.name: Izgnanie, the Smoldering
Izgnanie, the Smoldering.notes: "Izgnanie, the Smoldering" floats above the highest level of lava at the north end of Sunset Falls in Cauldros.

Experimental Second-Gen Zig.name: Experimental Second-Gen Zig
Experimental Second-Gen Zig.notes: "Experimental Second-Gen Zig" guards a bridge into kitsune base, a ganglion base that can be found in the south east of Cauldros (south of T'phnom Shelf).

Chantai's Galdr.name: Chantai's Galdr
Chantai's Galdr.notes: "Chantai's Galdr" patrols the western side of O'rrh Sim Castle Ruins around the ramped areas in Cauldros during the day.

Hayreddin, the Territorial.name: Hayreddin, the Territorial
Hayreddin, the Territorial.notes: "Hayreddin, the Territorial" can be found in the East Gate Plan in east Primordia. During the day it can be found wandering near the beach and during the night it can be found sleeping on a large rock with other Simius. It has low HP for its level but activates long invincibility periods making prolonged fights a pain to survive.

Climati, the Chilling Wind.name: Climati, the Chilling Wind
Climati, the Chilling Wind.notes: "Climati, the Chilling Wind" can be found strolling around the Central Ibra Ravine in eastern Oblivia.

Valeriano, the Rolling Thunder.name: Valeriano, the Rolling Thunder
Valeriano, the Rolling Thunder.notes: "Valeriano, the Rolling Thunder" appears during EM Storms at the lake under the leaning ring to the south of Yawning Giant (the huge bottomless pit) in Oblivia.

Silvestre, the Morning Light.name: Silvestre, the Morning Light
Silvestre, the Morning Light.notes: "Silvestre, the Morning Light" is at Oblivia's South Coast near the giant ring protruding from the ocean.

Thaddaeus, the Ultramafic.name: Thaddaeus, the Ultramafic
Thaddaeus, the Ultramafic.notes: "Thaddaeus, the Ultramafic" burrows up out of the ground between Lake Ciel and Cleansing Spring in south easy Sylvalum. As with other Cinicula it has a lot of HP and strong defences but while it isn't too dangerous by itself it lives in the path of a wandering Xe-Dom making a prolonged fight potentially dangerous.

Jindriska, the Serene.name: Jindriska, the Serene
Jindriska, the Serene.notes: "Jindriska, the Serene" is in the ground on the southern ridge of Twin Arches, a pair of bridges and ridges in North West Oblivia. Twin Arches is too minor of an area to appear on the mini map but can be found near the mountain to the north west of Cliffside Camp. Check for the location name in the top right of the TV screen under Oblivia.

Bertrand, the Gorge Scourge.name: Bertrand, the Gorge Scourge
Bertrand, the Gorge Scourge.notes: "Bertrand, the Gorge Scourge" clings to a wall inside an oasis like chamber that can be found half way along a tight passage to the east of Central Ibra Ravine in east Oblivia. Must approach it to provoke it into combat. There's a ton of Germivores in there so either don't use any AoEs or use enough AoEs to slaughter everything in there (the latter is much more fun).

Duran's Galdr.name: Duran's Galdr
Duran's Galdr.notes: "Duran's Galdr" appears during the late night (midnight to morning) above lotus keep building site, a ganglion base at Bloodpond Basin in the north of Noctilum.

Pharsis, the Everqueen.name: Pharsis, the Everqueen
Pharsis, the Everqueen.notes: "Pharsis, the Everqueen" sleeps inside the giant sphere in Sylvalum. There is a hole in there sphere facing the lake that can be flown through. The water inside is too deep to stand in but Pharsis can be fought on foot by either luring it to the entry tunnel or by standing on one of the many small floating spheres. Has 9.9 million HP and will kick your ass with an high damaging AoE attack that can wipe the entire party (Skells are immune to all damage during cockpit mode).

Sharnaak, the Technician.name: Sharnaak, the Technician
Sharnaak, the Technician.notes: "Sharnaak, the Technician" will appear at night on the southern path that ascends Mount M'gando in Cauldros (at the dormant Xe-dom). He is guarded by two Rhenium Oc-srvs.

Sadar, the Unhinged.name: Sadar, the Unhinged
Sadar, the Unhinged.notes: "Sadar, the Unhinged" appears during the night at the top of the joined towers in the south end of hilal stronghold, a ganglion base located south of Hilal Meadow in southern Sylvalum.

Hiro, the Priceless.name: Hiro, the Priceless
Hiro, the Priceless.notes: "Hiro, the Priceless" appears at night and clings to a green crystal in the south west corner of sandsprint cavity, the hidden room inside the mountain between Badr Basin and Lake Ciel in Sylvalum. It has to be provoked before it can be targeted. Get close or bump it with a Skell to do so. Despite being a golden Blatta it can be difficult to see. Access sandsprint cavity with a flying Skell at the passage to the south of Badr Basin.

Coil, the Never-Ending.name: Coil, the Never-Ending
Coil, the Never-Ending.notes: "Coil, the Never-Ending" can be found charging up during EM storms far above the ground at the centre of Dragonebone Promontory in Cauldros.

Vainamo, the Bellower.name: Vainamo, the Bellower
Vainamo, the Bellower.notes: "Vainamo, the Bellower" can be found in one of the craters at the Capital Wreckage area Cauldros.

Anselm, the Triumphant.name: Anselm, the Triumphant
Anselm, the Triumphant.notes: "Anselm, the Triumphant" is a big guy that wanders around Delusians South Summit in the east of Sylvalum.

Vorpall, the Sickle-Fanged.name: Vorpall, the Sickle-Fanged
Vorpall, the Sickle-Fanged.notes: "Vorpall, the Sickle-Fanged" resides within banshee cave the entrance of which is guarded by two oc-servs to the north west of Anvil Sandplain in northern Sylvalum. From the entrance simply take a right followed by a left to find Vorpall near a large group of Crystal Blatta on the floor (may take a moment for Vorpall to load in).

Dui, the Invaluable.name: Dui, the Invaluable
Dui, the Invaluable.notes: "Dui, the Invaluable" is in the north west most corner of the devils colony cave system which can be entered a short ways east of Oblivia Ingress at the north end of Yawning Giant. At each junction go north, east, north and then west down the long tunnel to find Dui, the Invaluable crawling in a small pool of water at the end.

Feld, the Indigo-Clad.name: Feld, the Indigo-Clad
Feld, the Indigo-Clad.notes: "Feld, the Indigo-Clad" can be found in a short side tunnel towards the south west corner of the secluded lava lake cavern in west Sylvalum.

Libra, the Long-Lived.name: Libra, the Long-Lived
Libra, the Long-Lived.notes: "Libra, the Long-Lived" is at the North Coast in Oblivia. For a level 20 it has a lot of HP like the rest of the Purgovent species.

Frontline Surveillance Zig.name: Frontline Surveillance Zig
Frontline Surveillance Zig.notes: "Frontline Surveillance Zig" keeps guard over a small island out in the ocean to the north west of Sylvalum.

Elaine, the Lunar Eclipse.name: Elaine, the Lunar Eclipse
Elaine, the Lunar Eclipse.notes: "Elaine, the Lunar Eclipse" appears during the night to fly around in the north west corner of Lake Basel in Oblivia.

Mikulas, the Keystone.name: Mikulas, the Keystone
Mikulas, the Keystone.notes: "Mikulas, the Keystone" can be found partially buried in the ground near the center of a patch of spiked crystals to the west of Lake Ciel in Sylvalum. There are several other Falsaxum but only Mikulas is next to a semisphere. Approach to wake it up.

Agito, the Golden.name: Agito, the Golden
Agito, the Golden.notes: "Agito, the Golden" clings to a wall during the night high in the rocky roofed area near where the starting area in south west Primordia. A Skell or some trick jumping will be required to get up above the small canyon. Have to get close to provoke it in order to start the fight.

Alithios, the Indignant.name: Alithios, the Indignant
Alithios, the Indignant.notes: "Alithios, the Indignant" is a large lava golem that appears during brimstone rain and stands at the top of Mount M'gando in Cauldros. Be careful not to fly too high and attract the unwanted attention of Vortice, the Deific Blast.

Vegetal, the Heatcrux.name: Vegetal, the Heatcrux
Vegetal, the Heatcrux.notes: "Vegetal, the Heatcrux" is a large flower that sits in an isolated, round'ish pool of lava just to the east of Titans Table in Cauldros.

Celestin, the Spring Storm.name: Celestin, the Spring Storm
Celestin, the Spring Storm.notes: "Celestin, the Spring Storm" can be found resting at headwater summit up above the waterfalls at Biahno Lake in western Primordia.

Spaniel, the Obedient.name: Spaniel, the Obedient
Spaniel, the Obedient.notes: "Spaniel, the Obedient" is part of a small pack of Caro under the command of Duran, the Draconian and appears throughout the day as well as part way into the night. They can be found just north of T'phnom Shelf in Cauldros.

Enhanced Attack Seidr.name: Enhanced Attack Seidr
Enhanced Attack Seidr.notes: "Enhanced Attack Seidr" is being upgraded at kitsune base, the ganglion base south of T'phnom Shelf in Cauldros (at FN Site 512).

Leva'el, the Terminus.name: Leva'el, the Terminus
Leva'el, the Terminus.notes: "Leva'el, the Terminus" is a postgame boss that can be found very high in the sky directly above a sandy island out in the ocean to the south west of Cauldros (the same island where Armed Recon Galdr can be found).

Berthold, the Blue-Eyed.name: Berthold, the Blue-Eyed
Berthold, the Blue-Eyed.notes: "Berthold, the Blue-Eyed" resides in sandsprint cavity, a cave hidden in the passage through the mountain between Lake Ciel and Baldr Basin in Sylvalum. The entrance is high up so flight is needed.

Ruth, the Shunner of Light.name: Ruth, the Shunner of Light
Ruth, the Shunner of Light.notes: "Ruth, the Shunner of Light" can be found down near the lava in the Secluded Lava Lake cavern in west Sylvalum. Use ranged attacks to lure it up. If that's too difficult just "Hop on in and fight him on foot!" as someone in /vg/ once advised.

Vortice, the Deific Blast.name: Vortice, the Deific Blast
Vortice, the Deific Blast.notes: "Vortice, the Deific Blast" can be found during brimstone rain in the thick smoke above the Mount M'gando volcano in Cauldros. Has close to 8.5 million HP.

Pelicollo, the Panzer.name: Pelicollo, the Panzer
Pelicollo, the Panzer.notes: "Pelicollo, the Panzer" creeps up and down a rocky passage along the top of the wall that separates Dragonbone Promontory and Sunset Falls in south Cauldros.

Sacrum, the Noctilucent.name: Sacrum, the Noctilucent
Sacrum, the Noctilucent.notes: "Sacrum, the Noctilucent" appears during the night at the hidden spring "whale's weeper" in the southern part of Noctilum. Whale's weeper can be entered from a small side path at waterway tangle just to the east of Old Dragontail Tree.

Melanya, the Sound Sleeper.name: Melanya, the Sound Sleeper
Melanya, the Sound Sleeper.notes: "Melanya, the Sound Sleeper" can be found sleeping at Oblivia Ingress, the entrance to Oblivia when walking from Primordia.

Archibolt, the Revolutionary.name: Archibolt, the Revolutionary
Archibolt, the Revolutionary.notes: "Archibolt, the Revolutionary" will appear during rainy weather on the small island in the south east of Biahno Lake which is to the west of NLA in Primordia. To quickly change the weather simply Fast Travel on the gamepad to refresh the area which causes the game to pick a new weather at random. The Return to Skell menu option works just the same.

Aria, the Zauberflote.name: Aria, the Zauberflote
Aria, the Zauberflote.notes: "Aria, the Zauberflote" is a trumpet bird hanging around the north side of Old Dragontail Tree in southern Noctilum.

Buchwald, the Guardian.name: Buchwald, the Guardian
Buchwald, the Guardian.notes: "Buchwald, the Guardian" guards some salvage treasures in the same room as FN Site 224's probe in Noctilum. It has incredible regenerative capabilities.

Pizelle, the Purple Lightning.name: Pizelle, the Purple Lightning
Pizelle, the Purple Lightning.notes: "Pizelle, the Purple Lightning" waits to ambush players on the cliff side path "dead man's ingress" to the north of Dead Mans Gulch in the north east of Noctilum.

Claire, the Sheltered.name: Claire, the Sheltered
Claire, the Sheltered.notes: "Claire, the Sheltered" can be found at the grassy area north west of Middle Hushflood in Noctilum and is the first half of the pair of Ovis that Pyotr, the Shepherd guards.

Fernando, the Immovable.name: Fernando, the Immovable
Fernando, the Immovable.notes: "Fernando, the Immovable" can be found during the day at Decapotamon around the centre of Noctilum.

Jia Mian, the Beloved.name: Jia Mian, the Beloved
Jia Mian, the Beloved.notes: "Jia Mian, the Beloved" can be found in the sky north east of Mount M'gando in Cauldros close to the walkways that are at about half the height of the mountain. The nearby round cage has some Storm Jacul that will agro when their beloved Jia Mian is attacked and vice versa.

Gadaf, the Pulverizer.name: Gadaf, the Pulverizer
Gadaf, the Pulverizer.notes: "Gadaf, the Pulverizer" can be found checking the falling sand in north ant's nest, a cave that can be accessed to the south of Cliffside Camp in Oblivia.

Caesar, the Hundred-Eyed.name: Caesar, the Hundred-Eyed
Caesar, the Hundred-Eyed.notes: "Caesar, the Hundred-Eyed" is on a stone bridge near the ceiling of "stonelattice cavern", a cavern accessed from halfway up the side of the cliff facing the northern ocean waters in the north west corner of Primordia. Flight required unless you want to trick jump into the cavern and use high range weapons but its honestly easier just to get flight.

Bohdan, the Mistral.name: Bohdan, the Mistral
Bohdan, the Mistral.notes: "Bohdan, the Mistral" will fly around the top of Unicorn Rock in north west Primordia during the day. Unicorn Rock is a very tall and slender mountain so flight is required to reach the Auravis roost near the top.
