Ajira Melon.name: Ajira Melon
Ajira Melon.description: A gourd-like vegetable encased in a black rind. The spongy, white insides have no taste at all, and are mostly used as a source of various vitamins.

Cranjelly.name: Cranjelly
Cranjelly.description: Its transparent skin encases a jelly like granulated fruit. The juice may be sweet, but it is also extremely sticky and a real chore to clean. Handle with care!

Starlight Apple.name: Starlight Apple
Starlight Apple.description: Beneath the black skin lies a seed that sparkles like a star, but also finds itself primed to go supernova. Sadly, removing the seed causes the fruit it to lose its trademark glow.

Sweet Nerine.name: Sweet Nerine
Sweet Nerine.description: A flower that blooms only for a single fleeting moment each day before shying away come nightfall. Its color is truly magnificent for those lucky enough to witness it.

Golden Sardine.name: Golden Sardine
Golden Sardine.description: A excitable golden fish that is often seen leaping free of the water. Its taste resembles that of an Earth sardine.

Keppo Carrot.name: Keppo Carrot
Keppo Carrot.description: A carrot that splits into eight roots. Seven of these are ultra sweet, while the remaining one takes on a bitterness that makes even the most stoic eyes water.

Arnacian Orewood.name: Arnacian Orewood
Arnacian Orewood.description: A diamond-like material that grows like bamboo on rainy days. It disappears when exposed to starlight.

Hummingstone.name: Hummingstone
Hummingstone.description: A curious stone that emits a mellifluous hum. When this melody was heard by the native Mirans, it would inevitably lead to a raucous dance party.

Anhydrous Radiator.name: Anhydrous Radiator
Anhydrous Radiator.description: A radiator from the White Whale that requires no coolant. It can be easily converted for use in cars and other vehicles.

Kiran Catnip.name: Kiran Catnip
Kiran Catnip.description: An alluring type of grass that has the power to entrance more than just felines. Its potent aroma attracts all manner of wildlife from miles around.

Crawling Bat.name: Crawling Bat
Crawling Bat.description: A giant quadruped bat that uses its non-functional wings to pull its way along the ground in search of food. Vulnerable in the dark, it tends to rest only in well-lit areas.

Zizi Rabbit.name: Zizi Rabbit
Zizi Rabbit.description: A three-eared, gunpowder-eating hare. Sweeping battlefields of every last spent bullet, their moniker of \"The Janitor\" is apt. Their numbers have recently spiked.

Zesian Fleawort.name: Zesian Fleawort
Zesian Fleawort.description: A grass that immediately regenerates upon being cut. If chopped, each piece will grow into yet more grass, making incineration the only proven method of disposal.

Ancient Allure.name: Ancient Allure
Ancient Allure.description: Covered in jumbled and indecipherable lettering, these cylindrical objects have been found scattered across Mira. The Pathfinder Clarissa gave them this name while struggling to decode them.

Hemp Wallet.name: Hemp Wallet
Hemp Wallet.description: A purse used by the ancient inhabitants of Mira. Listen to the jingle of the coins! If the previous owner had good luck with money, maybe a new owner will as well...

Grosium Core.name: Grosium Core
Grosium Core.description: An orb that emits a rather sinister glow. It possesses vast amounts of energy, but is harmful to humans.

Stretching Locust.name: Stretching Locust
Stretching Locust.description: A locust that uses its retractable antennae to gather food. It lacks the jumping ability of its Earth namesake, instead using its legs to drag itself around.

Multi-speckled Ladybug.name: Multi-speckled Ladybug
Multi-speckled Ladybug.description: An insect that looks like a ladybug. Its spots increase in number as it ages, until it becomes fully black in its final years. It has an odd hatred for music, and will flee at the first note of a song.

Centrifugal Beam Generator.name: Centrifugal Beam Generator
Centrifugal Beam Generator.description: An artificial-gravity generator that produces a rotating beam. It allows the crew of a ship to live and work while in a zero-gravity environment.

Vagabond Ant.name: Vagabond Ant
Vagabond Ant.description: Solitary ants that wander across Mira seeking out their next home. Parenthood is a brief affair, with barely a day's rest before resuming their journey.

Amidresian Tomato.name: Amidresian Tomato
Amidresian Tomato.description: A tomato that is able to hold impressive amounts of water. It appears only on rainy days, when its juicy flesh is enjoyed by many local indigens.

Nirvana Jonquil.name: Nirvana Jonquil
Nirvana Jonquil.description: A white flower with a modest bloom. Its height is unremarkable, as is its appearance. Yet once uprooted, it shines with an almost divine light.

Coaletri.name: Coaletri
Coaletri.description: A small, sleepy, koala-like animal with a number of wings on its back. These would be more useful if the animal wasn't so lazy.

Rizattice.name: Rizattice
Rizattice.description: Similar in appearance to a lizard—but almost completely desiccated due to an inability to store moisture. As such, it tends to hunt prey with high water content.

Meditation Powder.name: Meditation Powder
Meditation Powder.description: A chemical powder made of an unknown element. When the Harrier Bozé gave it a sniff, he felt it improved his concentration, and thus decided to give it this name.

High Accelerator.name: High Accelerator
High Accelerator.description: A small alien jetpack that allows the user to flee from confrontation at absurd speeds.

Fillal Filth.name: Fillal Filth
Fillal Filth.description: The crystallized excrement of unidentified microorganisms that has turned transparent and now resembles a beautiful crystal.

Sanelac Pearl.name: Sanelac Pearl
Sanelac Pearl.description: A hard pearl formed from minerals in subterranean rivers. It glimmers white in darkness, but appears transparent when placed under light.

Flecked Bottle.name: Flecked Bottle
Flecked Bottle.description: A mottled flask seemingly used to safely store precious liquid. Its seal has long since been broken, making its former contents a mystery for the ages.

Noranlily.name: Noranlily
Noranlily.description: A white lily that, when bathed in the light of the moon, emits a faint golden glow. Drawn towards its bloom, many types of  insect are often found around its flower.

Grinding Squirrel.name: Grinding Squirrel
Grinding Squirrel.description: A squirrel-like creature that uses extremely sharp teeth to carve a home in caves. If you venture into their lair, you're bound to come across their fearsome leader.

Logunie's Driftwood.name: Logunie's Driftwood
Logunie's Driftwood.description: Floating wood that swells up like a balloon as it absorbs water. Used by creatures such as the vagabond ant to travel downstream.

Crush Ring.name: Crush Ring
Crush Ring.description: A cruel alien torture device that coils around the head, arms, and legs, severely constricting the victim.

Acorn Abacus.name: Acorn Abacus
Acorn Abacus.description: A counting frame that uses acorns for beads, leading to speculation that the native creators had some sort of financial system.

Ball Mosquito.name: Ball Mosquito
Ball Mosquito.description: What looks like a small rubber ball flying through the air is in fact a mosquito. Its countless hair-covered mouths draw  blood from a whole host of creatures.

Facewood.name: Facewood
Facewood.description: A living mask made from the bark of a Miran tree. The bark grows in union with the face of the wearer, and was thought holy by ancient peoples for this reason.

Auroran Bone.name: Auroran Bone
Auroran Bone.description: A rarely-sighted item seen in polar skies. Its origin and classification remain a mystery to everyone.

Heatproof Inox Pipe.name: Heatproof Inox Pipe
Heatproof Inox Pipe.description: Plumbing used on the White Whale. It's made from an experimental form of stainless steel that is believed to be eternally rust- and corrosion-proof, no matter the external environment.

Rock-Orange.name: Rock-Orange
Rock-Orange.description: An orange easily mistaken for a rock. It  may have a soft and sumptuous taste, but many find it hard to look past its rather unappealing appearance.

Sadelana Lettuce.name: Sadelana Lettuce
Sadelana Lettuce.description: A heat-emitting lettuce whose flickering leaves resemble the sun. Oddly prone to self-combustion, it can only be found on rainy days.

Mondcherry.name: Mondcherry
Mondcherry.description: Ingestion may cause feelings of euphoria, with side effects including chest thumping and shrieks of joy. However, its intense spice should be taken into consideration.

Doga Dandelion.name: Doga Dandelion
Doga Dandelion.description: This dandelion fires its seed at nearby wildlife, whereupon the seeds feed parasitically on their host. Accordingly, the life of the host is rarely long.

Ashizel.name: Ashizel
Ashizel.description: A large, snail-like, shelled creature. The shell contains a store of fatty blubber that is used for sustenance in times of severe famine.

T-ray Light.name: T-ray Light
T-ray Light.description: A prototype high-tech device that allows the user to see through walls. It seems like true cutting-edge technology, but is unfortunately broken.

Tractor Beetle.name: Tractor Beetle
Tractor Beetle.description: A foot-long beetle with horns far tougher than those of its Earth namesake. It's usually able to take on any attackers who dare to challenge it.

Deflection Shield Mirror.name: Deflection Shield Mirror
Deflection Shield Mirror.description: Originally designed to defend against the alien onslaught, it failed in its application when it overheated. It was eventually recycled as part of the White Whale's shield system.

White Iron Sand.name: White Iron Sand
White Iron Sand.description: Sand with a high iron concentration. The process to extract this iron still eludes New LA scientists, though they are hard at work on new techniques.

Mosa Cabbage.name: Mosa Cabbage
Mosa Cabbage.description: Its fine strands make a furball shape, while its colorful hue promises a taste far more exotic than the humble cabbage it resembles.

Sonar Lemon.name: Sonar Lemon
Sonar Lemon.description: An ultrasonic lemon whose calls are out of human hearing range. Miran natives who pick up on its wails can often be found desperately seeking out the source.

Meteo Eater.name: Meteo Eater
Meteo Eater.description: A beetle-like insect that uses meteor shock waves as sustenance. It is able to instinctively seek out and locate potential landing zones prior to any meteorfall.

Assassin Springtail.name: Assassin Springtail
Assassin Springtail.description: A fist-shaped springtail whose poison grows in potency with each day. In times of health their shell appears pink, though it completely bleaches out upon death.

US-X Space Suit.name: US-X Space Suit
US-X Space Suit.description: A suit that can withstand the vacuum of space for over 24 hours. This was considered to be the height of technology at the time of the White Whale's launch.

Jagged Mortar.name: Jagged Mortar
Jagged Mortar.description: A mortar lined with tiny spurs that was used by local natives for making medicine. One can use the attached pestle to crush contents with ease.

Sona Herb.name: Sona Herb
Sona Herb.description: An herb with a sweet, fresh, and relaxing aroma. Even the most lively of creatures is said to be calmed by the scent.

Goddess's Kiss.name: Goddess's Kiss
Goddess's Kiss.description: A carved stone shaped in the image of a beautiful goddess. On occasion, a tear- like liquid flows from its eyes. Entranced by the object's beauty, the Outfitter Christopher came up with its name.

California Sunset.name: California Sunset
California Sunset.description: A spherical crystal that shimmers with the baked orange glow of a California dusk. The Pathfinder Corwin named it in memory of the sunsets he saw as a child back in his home state.

L-002 Fuel Tank.name: L-002 Fuel Tank
L-002 Fuel Tank.description: A fuel tank that formed part of the White Whale's propulsion drive system. It is said to be the height of fuel- compression technology.

Mirage Scope.name: Mirage Scope
Mirage Scope.description: The image presented to those who peer into this eyepiece is rarely consistent with reality. In fact, some of the views have been truly out-of-this world, which is why the Outfitter Camber gave it this name.

Garudo Pellionia Minima.name: Garudo Pellionia Minima
Garudo Pellionia Minima.description: Although this plant grows throughout the land, its large seed often sprouts in narrow crevices, resulting in it becoming blocked off. It's considered an endangered species as a result.

L-002 Space Analyzer.name: L-002 Space Analyzer
L-002 Space Analyzer.description: This instrument analyzes the atmosphere. It also scans for microbial life, which can indicate whether or not a planet is inhabited.

Lacey Potato.name: Lacey Potato
Lacey Potato.description: A teardrop-shaped potato found in Primordia. Extremely bitter, it's unsuited for direct use in food, but is often used as a source of protein in processed foods.

Strawlenny.name: Strawlenny
Strawlenny.description: A fruit that looks like a burdock, but tastes like a strawberry. It usually undergoes processing into a strawberry form in order to please a picky public.

Socha Guava.name: Socha Guava
Socha Guava.description: A palm-sized fruit that grows wild in the woods of Noctilum. Continued exposure to the sun's rays will dissolve the skin and  reveal the flesh within.

Timid Sunflower.name: Timid Sunflower
Timid Sunflower.description: A short flower which, despite its name, avoids the sunlight at all costs. Forcing light upon it, however, will cause it to grow quite tall.

Babaco Leaf.name: Babaco Leaf
Babaco Leaf.description: An unusually broad-leaved and sturdy plant that aggressively propagates itself, shoving aside other plants and even rocks as it grows.

False Cedar.name: False Cedar
False Cedar.description: A large grass that at first glance looks like a tree. Contrary to appearances, however, it is extremely flexible and surprisingly easy to cut.

Iguari.name: Iguari
Iguari.description: An iguana-like creature with a long, extendable tongue that it uses as a fishing rod. The very best hunters go on to become boss iguari, dividing their species.

Bananaleaf.name: Bananaleaf
Bananaleaf.description: A dull looking, banana-flavored leaf.  Although loved by all for its flavor, its habit of camouflaging itself as just another leaf makes it a rather rare find.

Godmelon.name: Godmelon
Godmelon.description: A rare, light-emitting melon. Worshiped since the dawn of time as a sacred fruit, a single bite of its flesh is said to inspire enlightenment. ...Or at least a smile.

Nostalgia L-002.name: Nostalgia L-002
Nostalgia L-002.description: A virtual reality helmet that allows the user to view scenes from Earth. Imperative for the morale of any crew on a lengthy space voyage.

Zandemo Eggplant.name: Zandemo Eggplant
Zandemo Eggplant.description: A sweet, tough eggplant that grows from trees and absorbs their sap. It also draws out pathogens from within the tree, thus increasing the life of its parent.

Mk. IX Hypercooler.name: Mk. IX Hypercooler
Mk. IX Hypercooler.description: A heat-processing device that was finished just before launch. It recycles heat energy produced by the engine which would otherwise have been wasted.

Sleeping Amaryllis.name: Sleeping Amaryllis
Sleeping Amaryllis.description: With petals that take on the color of their surroundings, these flowers can be inordinately difficult to locate.

Flowering Morrow Fern.name: Flowering Morrow Fern
Flowering Morrow Fern.description: A plant with seemingly self-aware mouthed tendrils that extend outwards to hunt nearby insects. Rich in protein, they are in turn a source of nourishment for others.

Rock Armadillo.name: Rock Armadillo
Rock Armadillo.description: A creature that curls into a ball when attacked, using its rocklike appearance as camouflage. Burdened by its own weight as it grows, its final days are reduced to only the tiniest movements.

Fodornallow Greens.name: Fodornallow Greens
Fodornallow Greens.description: Flora that grows by absorbing plasma from the surrounding atmosphere. Its deep taste and numbing effects are coveted by chefs and foodies everywhere.

Resonating Madonater.name: Resonating Madonater
Resonating Madonater.description: An electromagnetic device used by shape-shifting aliens. It interferes with the sensory perception of other individuals in the area.

Morphling Flounder.name: Morphling Flounder
Morphling Flounder.description: A flat fish with a movable eye that allows it to resemble both a left-eyed and right- eyed flounder.

Loathsome Blob.name: Loathsome Blob
Loathsome Blob.description: The Nopon put this stinky ball in their pocket to repel would-be predators with its rank odor.

Gesture Glove.name: Gesture Glove
Gesture Glove.description: An electronic glove interface which allows linked devices to be controlled remotely by the user's hand movements.

Logunie's Driftwood Boat.name: Logunie's Driftwood Boat
Logunie's Driftwood Boat.description: A tub-shaped Nopon boat fashioned from buoyant driftwood. Historically used by the Nopon to explore the oceans.

Sour Plum.name: Sour Plum
Sour Plum.description: A sour plum that only grows in dark caves. Its taste can reduce even the hardiest of creatures to their knees, and sends most fleeing in terror.

Eternal Moss.name: Eternal Moss
Eternal Moss.description: This moss, which grows on the giant trees of Noctilum, falls and settles like snow. It is a great insulator, and is often used by small animals as bedding in winter.

Primitive Colossus Statue.name: Primitive Colossus Statue
Primitive Colossus Statue.description: A pair of gigantic stone idols locked in combat. No one is sure who sculpted them or gave them their name, but their primal beauty often leaves a deep impression on those who stand before them.

Lea Lily.name: Lea Lily
Lea Lily.description: A plant with a tough, silver-colored flower that chimes like a bell upon catching the wind. Its clear tones offer visitors to Noctilum a brief moment of serenity.

Noctilucent Dragonfly.name: Noctilucent Dragonfly
Noctilucent Dragonfly.description: A luminescent dragonfly from Noctilum. To attract females, the male radiates in a spectacular light show that signals the beginning of courtship.

Strobing Horsefly.name: Strobing Horsefly
Strobing Horsefly.description: A light-emitting horsefly. The more blood it drinks, the brighter and wilder it gets. Even a single glimpse of its strobe sends the doragaroos of Oblivia fleeing.

Gleaming Magnet.name: Gleaming Magnet
Gleaming Magnet.description: Named by the Curator Jengo, this mysterious object contains a multitude of magnetic stones that orbit erratically within its cube-like frame.

Fraudulent Mirror.name: Fraudulent Mirror
Fraudulent Mirror.description: A compact radar that flashes with multiple points of interest, though nothing is ever found at the indicated spots. The Mediator Lara Nara named the device while putting on his makeup.

Galjim Crystal.name: Galjim Crystal
Galjim Crystal.description: An orb that displays future and past flora and fauna of Mira. Unfortunately, all that can usually be seen is a motionless plant or grazing beast.

Hexagauge.name: Hexagauge
Hexagauge.description: A honeycomb-shaped body-scanning device used by insectoid aliens.

Spherical EM Motor.name: Spherical EM Motor
Spherical EM Motor.description: The space enclosed within this transparent box supports a floating spherical object, the constant rotation of which produces a never-ending supply of kinetic energy. Named rather plainly by the Curator May.

Madame Mantis.name: Madame Mantis
Madame Mantis.description: A hairy insect with a falciform front limb. With a higher proportion of females to males, many an epic battle takes place as females seek to secure a mate.

Pardo Spider.name: Pardo Spider
Pardo Spider.description: An inconspicuous eight-legged insect that is actually as heavy as iron. It uses silk from its eight legs to traverse the treetops of Noctilum at speed.

Brain Terminal.name: Brain Terminal
Brain Terminal.description: An alien device that interfaces directly with the brain. Not usable by humans.

3D Printer.name: 3D Printer
3D Printer.description: This machine can print solid materials such as basic parts and personal effects. One was assigned to each mechanic on the White Whale.

Madness Hornet.name: Madness Hornet
Madness Hornet.description: A hornet with a foot-long stinger that sends victims into hysteria. Animals stung by this hornet can often be seen raging through the forests of Noctilum.

Lava Mango.name: Lava Mango
Lava Mango.description: A fruit with rubberlike elasticity. Its skin has been used in the clothing  industry, while its sweet, chewy texture yields a sensation similar to that of gum.

Mirrored Peacock.name: Mirrored Peacock
Mirrored Peacock.description: A wild bird with mirrored wings. When hunted, they use these wings to reflect the sun's rays, dazzling their pursuers and granting a brief chance of escape.

Sibercaseras Mushroom.name: Sibercaseras Mushroom
Sibercaseras Mushroom.description: A subspecies of the caseras mushroom, which only appears once every 100 years. Those who taste it are said to live out their days in a pure, bliss-like state.

HI9 Ion Thruster.name: HI9 Ion Thruster
HI9 Ion Thruster.description: An advanced electronic propulsion system that allows for precise navigational control at ultra-high speeds.

Sea Anemone Platter.name: Sea Anemone Platter
Sea Anemone Platter.description: A shellfish plate used by ancient Nopon. Analysis of the residual material would surely give an idea of the ancient Nopon diet, but such investigations are low on the priority ladder at the moment.

Gluttonutan.name: Gluttonutan
Gluttonutan.description: This primate's belly pouch is used to hoard the many treasures which litter the forest floor. Fiercely protective, only the foolish would attempt to challenge it.

Harnenga Cotton.name: Harnenga Cotton
Harnenga Cotton.description: A cotton plant that grows in the shape of an arrow. A material of the finest quality, this cotton is very popular among the Nopon.

Absop's Swallowtail.name: Absop's Swallowtail
Absop's Swallowtail.description: A butterfly that survives on light emitted from the sun and fellow Noctilum residents. In its final throes of life, it bursts into a spectacular light show.

Continental Jellyfish.name: Continental Jellyfish
Continental Jellyfish.description: A land-roaming jellyfish with a soft, translucent body. Moving using its many tentacles, it wraps itself around its prey before absorbing them into its body.

Tenacious Moth.name: Tenacious Moth
Tenacious Moth.description: A moth that makes its own way in life. However, in amorous times, pairs can be seen rushing through their courtship dance as if their lives depended on it.

Katoan Leaf.name: Katoan Leaf
Katoan Leaf.description: A leaf that emits faint bursts of radiation. Found in Noctilum, these leaves can be used to shed light on other items.

Prapaya.name: Prapaya
Prapaya.description: Upon ripening, this fruit will dislodge itself from the tree and fall to the ground, causing serious injury to any unfortunate enough to be in the way.

Caseras Mushroom.name: Caseras Mushroom
Caseras Mushroom.description: This fungus from Noctilum releases spores that send nearby creatures into a daze. Its subspecies imparts a bliss-like state on all who consume it.

Noka Mirrorstone.name: Noka Mirrorstone
Noka Mirrorstone.description: A stone polished into a mirror by the constant trickle of water from a giant tree. Staring into it gives the sense of looking into one's own soul.

Joadtank.name: Joadtank
Joadtank.description: An entirely sterile tank completely devoid of any organisms or bacteria. How very dull.

Cane Soil.name: Cane Soil
Cane Soil.description: Dirt that contains significant amounts of sugar. It has a rather gritty aftertaste, but can be turned into a decent sweetener with enough processing.

Shiny Lamp.name: Shiny Lamp
Shiny Lamp.description: A Nopon lantern stuffed with luminescent katoan leaves. Harvesting leaves for this lamp is a labor of love for the many Nopon who still revere its gentle glow.

Kusakiri Stag Beetle.name: Kusakiri Stag Beetle
Kusakiri Stag Beetle.description: This creature attacks tractor beetles on sight. In all other cases, it uses its large pincers only for the peaceful cutting of grass blades.

Muneria Flower.name: Muneria Flower
Muneria Flower.description: No amount of plucking will stop this flower's petals from sprouting right back. It is said that eating it bestows similar effects, making it popular with the elderly.

Sekka Cosmos.name: Sekka Cosmos
Sekka Cosmos.description: A large cosmos plant whose petals move in response to stimulus. This has led many to believe that it may possess a certain degree of sentience.

Scales of Justice.name: Scales of Justice
Scales of Justice.description: When objects are placed upon the scales, they tip not from the actual weight, but from some other form of mass. The Mediator Justin declared this as \"measuring the weight of justice.\"

Earthfreezer.name: Earthfreezer
Earthfreezer.description: A capsule that stored a frozen genetic database of Earth plant and animal life. Much of this data was sadly lost in the crash of the White Whale.

Gluttonutan Clay.name: Gluttonutan Clay
Gluttonutan Clay.description: Clay formed from a mixture of gluttonutan droppings and Noctilum soil. It boasts unparalleled elasticity, and will not snap no matter how far it is stretched.

Chameleon Creeping Plant.name: Chameleon Creeping Plant
Chameleon Creeping Plant.description: An insectivorous plant that lures prey into its jaws with a sweet aroma. These fallen insects become flecks on the plant's body, eventually mottling each petal.

Amana Durian.name: Amana Durian
Amana Durian.description: A luminescent fruit that grows within the giant flowers of Noctilum. Adorned with long, sharp thorns, those that fall prey to its glow usually meet a painful end.

Gubura Cabbage Leaf.name: Gubura Cabbage Leaf
Gubura Cabbage Leaf.description: A vegetable that takes like cabbage. It sports an odd blackish tint that only intensifies when boiled.

Doragaroo.name: Doragaroo
Doragaroo.description: A small kangaroo-type creature able to leap many miles in a single jump. Its poor sense of direction often leads to it  overshooting its intended target.

Magical Finding Rod.name: Magical Finding Rod
Magical Finding Rod.description: A Nopon dowsing rod for locating mineral deposits and groundwater. A coin on one end wobbles when it hits its target. Hardly the most scientific of methods, but it seems to work for them.

Multi-mirror Solar Drone.name: Multi-mirror Solar Drone
Multi-mirror Solar Drone.description: This photovoltaic system generates power from solar energy. It was originally attached to the hull of the White Whale.

5th Gen Recycler.name: 5th Gen Recycler
5th Gen Recycler.description: This device harvests microbes and organic space materials, which are then recycled and converted into energy for the White Whale.

L-002 Degeneration Reactor.name: L-002 Degeneration Reactor
L-002 Degeneration Reactor.description: This mysterious reactor was the White Whale's primary generator, knowledge of which was strictly restricted to engineers directly involved in its operation.

Imposter Bug.name: Imposter Bug
Imposter Bug.description: A stink bug that resembles a Nopon from certain angles. The bug's cry is so intolerable to the Nopon, however, that they will do anything to avoid it.

Sand Cucumber.name: Sand Cucumber
Sand Cucumber.description: A sea-cucumber-like creature that absorbs sand into its body for its survival. With  90 percent of its body weight being sand, it is able to quickly fill in any wounds.

Shadow Fly.name: Shadow Fly
Shadow Fly.description: A fly that refracts ambient light, illuminating its surroundings for miles. Don't be fooled by its pretty appearance— this carnivorous insect is a real handful.

Common Stick Insect.name: Common Stick Insect
Common Stick Insect.description: This insect, almost indistinguishable from branches, chooses not to hide itself in this way. Instead, it adopts a brownish hue on green branches, and a green one on brown branches.

Angel Stone.name: Angel Stone
Angel Stone.description: A transparent stone that holds a fossilized, angelic-looking creature. Transfixed by its heavenly beauty, the Harrier Adelbert gave it its name.

Myuena Cactus.name: Myuena Cactus
Myuena Cactus.description: A cactus with thorns as soft as the tentacle of a jellyfish. It is said that if rotting myuena cacti come into contact with the rain, they turn into silvery cactaceous resin.

Jet Turtle.name: Jet Turtle
Jet Turtle.description: A turtle-like creature that feeds mainly on the zizi rabbit. Able to fit its entire body within its shell, it uses rotation to zip along at astonishing speeds.

Dobobora Broccoli.name: Dobobora Broccoli
Dobobora Broccoli.description: A crown-shaped broccoli that is said to bestow the lordship of Mira to those who eat it. Tests indicate that consumption does indeed lead to feelings of grandeur.

Phantom Tanuki.name: Phantom Tanuki
Phantom Tanuki.description: A beast with space-distorting camouflage that allows it to morph into other forms. Hanging fatty deposits allow it to survive during lean periods.

Thornbox.name: Thornbox
Thornbox.description: A box for storing Nopon pollen-collection tools that are used to attract insects. The pollen is eaten and recycled by the insects before then being harvested.

Sandstone Etching.name: Sandstone Etching
Sandstone Etching.description: A lithograph etched by an ancient desert civilization from Oblivia. As it is currently indecipherable, the fate met by this culture is still unknown.

Wainess Fossil.name: Wainess Fossil
Wainess Fossil.description: The fossilized remains of plants from Oblivia. It has similar properties to coal, and although it cannot be used as fuel, it is of use as research material.

Will Pepper.name: Will Pepper
Will Pepper.description: A pepper that flashes red, yellow, blue, and then black in a continuous sequence. It's a feast for both the eyes and the stomach.

Royal Grape.name: Royal Grape
Royal Grape.description: A fruit so large that only one grows per tree. Its juice can be mixed with alcohol to create a palatable, wine-like drink.

Silvery Cactaceous Resin.name: Silvery Cactaceous Resin
Silvery Cactaceous Resin.description: A claylike, soft silver ore that becomes hard when forged. Its origin is uncertain, but it is believed to come from decomposed myuena cacti.

Nopolith.name: Nopolith
Nopolith.description: A rectangular stone monument of perfect black. According to Nopon folklore, it brings great wisdom to any who dare touch it.

Denemozumi Mouse.name: Denemozumi Mouse
Denemozumi Mouse.description: The perfect species of mouse. When faced with adversity, they form into organized divisions and overpower their opponent with sheer numbers.

Fullbelly Gecko.name: Fullbelly Gecko
Fullbelly Gecko.description: A gecko-like reptile with a large appetite. The fatty globule revealed by peeling back its hard skin is highly prized for a high protein content and buttery taste.

Jobo Primrose.name: Jobo Primrose
Jobo Primrose.description: By allowing its flowers to be eaten by Miran wildlife, this plant is able to propagate by dispersing its seed via their excrement.

Horned Helmet.name: Horned Helmet
Horned Helmet.description: A large, primitive helmet made from a resilient-looking shell. Its two protruding horns inspire terror in battle.

Echo Rock.name: Echo Rock
Echo Rock.description: An obnoxious rock that throws your words right back at you. Good luck confronting it, though, since it is dull and featureless as...well, a stone. The Curator Jengo named it with a smile.

Illogical Etchings.name: Illogical Etchings
Illogical Etchings.description: A lithograph that appears to hold encoded blueprints for a Skell-like robotic machine. The engineer Tika named it in frustration after staying up all night failing to decipher its instructions.

Slasher Beetle.name: Slasher Beetle
Slasher Beetle.description: The most powerful beetle on the planet. It tears up foes with razor-sharp horns, and spits iron-piercing pellets for long- range strikes. Truly the king of the insects!

Kepha Holly.name: Kepha Holly
Kepha Holly.description: A holly with large purple fruit. These fruits explode upon impact, dispersing their stores of pollen. Certain creatures find the smell of this pollen intolerable.

Shinuyuni Garlic.name: Shinuyuni Garlic
Shinuyuni Garlic.description: A root with a tapered horn shape that requires thick gloves for proper handling. Eating it grants superb recovery properties, but also horrific breath.

Octo-suka.name: Octo-suka
Octo-suka.description: A land-dwelling octopus-like creature with eight enormously long legs. Its unusually low body weight makes it highly likely to fracture in stiff winds.

Blast Chard.name: Blast Chard
Blast Chard.description: This plant contains a unique bitterness that is coveted among gourmands and chefs of New LA. Even coffee-type drinks can be derived from this wonder ingredient.

Suna Watermelon.name: Suna Watermelon
Suna Watermelon.description: Growing only in the stormiest of climes, at first this fruit looks no different than a clump of sand. Once it ripens, however, it takes on the look of a watermelon.

Spine-O-Corrector.name: Spine-O-Corrector
Spine-O-Corrector.description: A spine-straightening device once very popular amongst the short-statured Nopon. It fell out of favor when its effects proved to be far more damaging than helpful.

Whip Scorpion.name: Whip Scorpion
Whip Scorpion.description: A long, soft-bodied scorpion that uses its whiplike tail to repel attackers. Constant use of the tail for various other endeavors has resulted in evolutionary loss of the stinger's venom.

Fleeting Baboon.name: Fleeting Baboon
Fleeting Baboon.description: An exceedingly hairy baboon-like creature. With a lifespan of less than a week, maturation and aging are both extremely rapid.

Spiked Pomegranate.name: Spiked Pomegranate
Spiked Pomegranate.description: A fruit covered in sharp thorns and prized for its blood-clotting effects. The bleeding its harvest causes, however, means more than a few are devoured in the field.

Kridokan Air.name: Kridokan Air
Kridokan Air.description: A mysterious green vapor secreted inside caves. It turns into oxygen once ventilated, and for this reason is of great interest to the scientists of New LA.

Cosse Bean.name: Cosse Bean
Cosse Bean.description: A thick casing houses multiple fist-sized beans. Eating just one provides a day's worth of nourishment, making them ideal for long journeys.

Zedis Twig.name: Zedis Twig
Zedis Twig.description: A small branch that attracts lightning. It's likely to have been used as a lightning rod due to this unique quality.

Kiwegg.name: Kiwegg
Kiwegg.description: A kiwi with an egg-like shell. This hard casing acts as a protective shield, guarding the inner contents against various Miran insects.

Beagflea Squash.name: Beagflea Squash
Beagflea Squash.description: A new gourd that arrived with an alien race. Despite its bland taste, its ability to grow in the most sterile of land makes it an invaluable foodstuff.

Charupa Leaves.name: Charupa Leaves
Charupa Leaves.description: A magnetically charged grass covered in iron dust. Its ability to remove excess iron from the body upon digestion makes it a widely used herbal remedy.

Eradicator Eyepiece.name: Eradicator Eyepiece
Eradicator Eyepiece.description: Goggles designed by giant aliens that transmit information and orders directly into the eye of the user.

Ultra Filter.name: Ultra Filter
Ultra Filter.description: A high-performance filtration machine that can create water from soil and sand. When the start button is pressed, a voice calls out, “Water-making time, right?” and music begins playing.

Gudo Rocambole.name: Gudo Rocambole
Gudo Rocambole.description: Similar to Earth's rocambole plant, but able to grow at an abnormal daily rate. This plant is quite short lived, and unable to proliferate as a result.

Steel Tail Sheath.name: Steel Tail Sheath
Steel Tail Sheath.description: An alien tail protector emblazoned with a clan crest. The quality of workmanship indicates that it once belonged to an individual of some status.

Exubera Stalactite.name: Exubera Stalactite
Exubera Stalactite.description: A sharp-tipped stalactite fragment.  It emits a beautiful ring of multicolored light, but careless touching may result in serious injury.

Warbone.name: Warbone
Warbone.description: A knuckle guard made from the skull of a fallen opponent. Its battle-worn look is accentuated by numerous scratches and dents that tell an epic story.

Ouroboros Bracelet.name: Ouroboros Bracelet
Ouroboros Bracelet.description: A dried snake that is eating its own tail. Used by the Nopon as a bracelet.

Chameleon Sand.name: Chameleon Sand
Chameleon Sand.description: Sand that is able to change its color— and with that, its taste. Ranging from salty when white to sweet when red, the possible variations are endless. Named by the Prospector Sarona.

Mya Oats.name: Mya Oats
Mya Oats.description: An unremarkable grass with emetic properties that cause those who ingest it to vomit. It can be used alternatively as either a medicine or poison.

Perished Stone Spear.name: Perished Stone Spear
Perished Stone Spear.description: A spear invented by an ancient species once they took to walking upright. Their enlightenment came at a cost, however, as the same weapon eventually sealed their demise.

Lost Memory Synthesizer.name: Lost Memory Synthesizer
Lost Memory Synthesizer.description: A machine to fuse crystals that conceal some sort of energy. The problem is, said crystals don't seem to exist. Upon realizing its uselessness, the Harrier Sara-Ariel named it in disappointment.

Moleworm.name: Moleworm
Moleworm.description: A worm that draws its nourishment from miranium, boring ever deeper into the planet in search of this energy source. As such, it is rarely seen above ground.

Strong Iron.name: Strong Iron
Strong Iron.description: A rust-ravaged iron column with a tensile strength that defies reason. Despite being rusted to the core, it can easily withstand loads many times that of standard iron. Named by the Curator Howard.

Maiden's Guardian Star.name: Maiden's Guardian Star
Maiden's Guardian Star.description: A jewel that sparkles like the first star of the evening. The Reclaimer Nastasha began wearing one as a charm to protect her companions, and the idea caught on with other BLADEs, leading to its name.

Drum of Valor.name: Drum of Valor
Drum of Valor.description: A drum made from the stomach of a beast. It is said to grant bravery to Nopon embarking on a lonely trek. If one listens close, they can almost hear it beating like a courageous heart.

Sacrificial Reactor.name: Sacrificial Reactor
Sacrificial Reactor.description: A furnace that faces the skies in prayer, probably used for religious rites and festivals. It contains what appears to be the remains of multiple sacrifices.

Cruise Deflector AiR.name: Cruise Deflector AiR
Cruise Deflector AiR.description: This device projected an energy field around the White Whale that acted as a protective shield against space junk.

Gormless Monkey.name: Gormless Monkey
Gormless Monkey.description: A small monkey with a featureless face, it relies on sound and movement to gain its bearings.

Bude Mugwort.name: Bude Mugwort
Bude Mugwort.description: Glistening leaves sprout from this plant's long, narrow stem. If blended with saliva, they produce a viscous liquid that coils around the throat and restricts breathing.

White Sand Beetle.name: White Sand Beetle
White Sand Beetle.description: A beetle-like creature that feeds on white sandy spores. It nests in the cliffs of Sylvalum, burrowing deep before packing itself next to its fellow beetles like so many sardines.

Taoman Acid.name: Taoman Acid
Taoman Acid.description: A chemical produced when rainwater reacts with an unknown airborne substance. It's harmless for living organisms, but can dissolve most inorganic matter.

Shia Cattleya.name: Shia Cattleya
Shia Cattleya.description: A flower that shines with the beauty of  the finest jewels. As it blooms by stealing nutrients from other nearby plants, it also doubles up as a handy weed killer.

Pomio Spore.name: Pomio Spore
Pomio Spore.description: A spore that floats through the skies of Sylvalum and attracts nearby atmospheric particles, giving it a gem-like sparkle.

Crystal Butterfly.name: Crystal Butterfly
Crystal Butterfly.description: A splendid butterfly that flies on vivid violet wings adorned with fine crystal scales. It's slow to reproduce, but boasts a lifespan of over 300 years.

Snowy Angelhair.name: Snowy Angelhair
Snowy Angelhair.description: A white, furry insect that drifted to Sylvalum on the wind. Indistinguishable from a spore, it is quite difficult to find— though it is said to bring luck to any who do so.

Spore Balloon.name: Spore Balloon
Spore Balloon.description: A spore repainted by the Nopon and sold as a child's balloon toy. Its value tanked when the true identity was finally discovered.

Starmaker.name: Starmaker
Starmaker.description: A black-box planetarium that projects an image of the galaxy Mira inhabits onto nearby surfaces. The Pathfinder Mondo named it as he gazed in abject silence at the projected stars.

Jagitos Copper.name: Jagitos Copper
Jagitos Copper.description: Extraordinary heat diffusivity properties give this substance the ability to maintain a negative temperature no matter what environment it is placed in.

Dosoram Bean.name: Dosoram Bean
Dosoram Bean.description: Beans that increase the effects of alcohol, often leading to dangerous results. Drinkers are advised to find a different bar snack if at all possible.

Dring Slick.name: Dring Slick
Dring Slick.description: This constantly moving mudflow was  originally thought to be an earthquake, but in fact, only the surface moves.  Insects can often be observed hitching a ride on the top.

Trying Crown.name: Trying Crown
Trying Crown.description: A tight-fitting crown that can only be removed by breaking it. Thought to have been used in torture.

Cluster Papaya.name: Cluster Papaya
Cluster Papaya.description: Brimming with energy, this mysterious fruit is prone to cataclysmic explosion upon impact. Tread carefully when harvesting.

Straw Buoy.name: Straw Buoy
Straw Buoy.description: A flotation device made from straw. Though it starts out as a huge straw ring, it rapidly shrinks to a more compact size when it contacts water.

Ruge Daikon.name: Ruge Daikon
Ruge Daikon.description: A radish with interlocking roots that resemble the DNA double helix. Its grand appearance is sadly not matched by its lame, radish-y taste.

Coldberry.name: Coldberry
Coldberry.description: A fruit that captures the surrounding cold air. So cold as to induce frostbite with a single touch, it can only be eaten after being brought to room temperature.

Grandan Rock.name: Grandan Rock
Grandan Rock.description: A rock that registers no value when placed on a scale. You still wouldn't be happy if someone chucked it at your head, however.

Spirit Wand.name: Spirit Wand
Spirit Wand.description: A branch adorned with hundreds of beautiful Miran flowers. It is used by the Nopon for spiritual worship.

Intelligent Liquid Metal.name: Intelligent Liquid Metal
Intelligent Liquid Metal.description: There is said to be a large body of high- level info embedded within this liquid metal. Unfortunately, the liquid is currently inert and remains just out of reach.

Baibai Beetle.name: Baibai Beetle
Baibai Beetle.description: This blue beetle takes to the skies one month after hatching and—for some unknown reason—flies until it reaches the point of exhaustion.

Yabuyabu Ointment.name: Yabuyabu Ointment
Yabuyabu Ointment.description: A plant-based ointment used by the Nopon. It fell out of favor when its medicinal effects were found to be negligible.

Cordless Transformer.name: Cordless Transformer
Cordless Transformer.description: A device that wirelessly transmits energy particles from one point to another. This functionality led to great space savings aboard the White Whale.

Decoy DNA.name: Decoy DNA
Decoy DNA.description: A uniquely effective device that emits false DNA signals in order to confuse pursuing hostile aliens.

Mizaria Celery.name: Mizaria Celery
Mizaria Celery.description: A rare type of celery that arises only from the crevices of deceased fauna soaked by incessant rain. Its taste depends entirely on the type of carcass from which it grew.

Flowering Egg.name: Flowering Egg
Flowering Egg.description: An egg-shaped object that plays host to a variety of different flower species. Upon witnessing said flowers breaking out from the egg's shell to bloom, a speechless Prospector called Gale gave it this name.

Hard Skin.name: Hard Skin
Hard Skin.description: A paper-thin protective material. Its toughness and resistance to heat belies its thickness.

White Cassis.name: White Cassis
White Cassis.description: A fruit that contains white, snowflake-like seeds. It has a harsh and bitter flavor, and is often used as a pick-me-up for those residing in colder climes.

Camocloak.name: Camocloak
Camocloak.description: The cloth used to make this cloak imitates its surroundings. It looks to have been invented by an advanced civilization that has since gone extinct.

L-002 Dagoo Heat Ray.name: L-002 Dagoo Heat Ray
L-002 Dagoo Heat Ray.description: A high-energy laser mounted on the White Whale. It has since been decommissioned, but the scars of battle still stain its scorched barrel.

A-HAB autonomous AI.name: A-HAB autonomous AI
A-HAB autonomous AI.description: A portion of the AI system installed on the White Whale. Reliable and sound of judgment, this essential component of the flight was unfortunately destroyed during the crash landing on Mira.

Acton Rock Shards.name: Acton Rock Shards
Acton Rock Shards.description: Despite being inanimate, these rocks appear to take root and grow. As a result, they are often mistaken for shrubs and trees.

Shimmering Skin.name: Shimmering Skin
Shimmering Skin.description: A high-tech lava suit made from unknown materials. Unfortunately, as it operates on biometrics it will destroy itself if worn by any species other than its original creator.

Brilliant Green Liquid.name: Brilliant Green Liquid
Brilliant Green Liquid.description: The liquid within this tube emits a brilliant green glow, but the unknown energy it produces is of no use in current weapons. The Prospector Leland Cole named it while laughing heartily.

Missile Wiring.name: Missile Wiring
Missile Wiring.description: Wiring composed of countless fiber cables. Using this wire allowed for free control of launched missiles.

Berzerker Unit.name: Berzerker Unit
Berzerker Unit.description: An item used to induce a rage-like state in battle. If given to one not able to tolerate the medication's effects, however, instant death is a certainty.

Thunderbolt Emblem.name: Thunderbolt Emblem
Thunderbolt Emblem.description: A banner emblazoned with the crest of a militaristic alien clan. Its content boasts of that particular group's achievements on the battlefield.

Beaporge.name: Beaporge
Beaporge.description: A small raccoon covered in soft fur that takes great pleasure in grooming its fellow creatures. It will even give Skells a scrub if given the chance.

Sese Lily.name: Sese Lily
Sese Lily.description: A plant with a ringed stem that emits a single soap bubble once a day. These bubbles carry pollen that gives birth to the next batch of sese lilies.

Diresheep.name: Diresheep
Diresheep.description: A sheep-like animal with abnormally long, soft fleece that is ideal for use in clothes. It's an unusually ill-tempered beast,  so approach with caution.

Stargazer.name: Stargazer
Stargazer.description: A long cylinder with carefully aligned stone lenses, often used as a telescope to view the stars. Unusually expensive for something that brings so much joy.

Affinity Soulchain.name: Affinity Soulchain
Affinity Soulchain.description: A chain of unbreakable triangular rings that are impossible to separate. Upon witnessing its unwavering strength, the Curator Quincy gave it this name to symbolize the bonds between friends.

Rainy Cricket.name: Rainy Cricket
Rainy Cricket.description: A giant cricket that sleeps in the sand and rarely ventures above the surface. Aggressive in its short waking hours, it will attack on sight.

Double Helical Salt.name: Double Helical Salt
Double Helical Salt.description: A mysterious white object with a double helical structure. The Curator Caracas discovered and named it, but died of poisoning after tasting it.

Pale Maize.name: Pale Maize
Pale Maize.description: A blue-white crop with an appearance similar to corn. As the plant grows, its seeds fill with gas before finally detaching and drifting away on the wind.

Penginion.name: Penginion
Penginion.description: A bird covered in mysterious markings. Intelligent enough to understand language, it can easily avoid all but the most clever of predators.

Detilid Device.name: Detilid Device
Detilid Device.description: An excessively large hoop-shaped device that equips to the arm. The alien tech and size of the device mean that it is not easily handled by human operators.

Shido Persimmon.name: Shido Persimmon
Shido Persimmon.description: A lack of flesh is made up for by numerous edible seeds. Although bitter, they are also quite addictive, causing eaters to devour them without pause.

Yaya Sesame.name: Yaya Sesame
Yaya Sesame.description: The casing of this plant contains seeds finer than a grain of sand. Shaking it produces a pleasant rhythmic sound that is sure to calm moods and relieve stress.

Medusa Squid.name: Medusa Squid
Medusa Squid.description: A squid-like creature with 20 tentacles sprouting from its head. Though it often attacks other creatures, it rarely emerges victorious.

Emerald Grape.name: Emerald Grape
Emerald Grape.description: A grape with patterned, jewellike seeds. Though for the most part immensely sour, it is also known to turn sweet on rare occasions—bringing joy to all who eat it.

Fullerene Coral.name: Fullerene Coral
Fullerene Coral.description: A tree-like, land-based coral. Care is needed when handling, as the fragile coral breaks quite easily.

Glassy Cricket.name: Glassy Cricket
Glassy Cricket.description: A cricket with a gossamer-thin shell. Handle with extreme care, as this fragile insect will often shatter when caught.

Hello Transmitter.name: Hello Transmitter
Hello Transmitter.description: This looks like some kind of transmitting device, but no one knows where it is transmitting to. The Interceptor Ada named it after mumbling “hello, hello” into it numerous times with no response.

Queen's Rapture.name: Queen's Rapture
Queen's Rapture.description: A snowy white, angelic feather that shimmers with an air of refined nobility. The Harrier Grette gave the item its name as she gazed at it, enraptured.

Stone Screw.name: Stone Screw
Stone Screw.description: A screw made of stone that—despite being entirely natural in origin—can actually be used as in the way the name suggests. After naming it, the Pathfinder Astea did in fact put it to use as a screw.

Exploding Pansy.name: Exploding Pansy
Exploding Pansy.description: A flower that emits an explosive sound when it detects any type of noise nearby. Stalk it like a ninja unless you want to be blown to kingdom come.

Antorus Rose.name: Antorus Rose
Antorus Rose.description: A rose with petals that can be used as dyes—which can then be combined to form any color on the spectrum. It is said that these vivid colors will never fade.

Zalon Dirt.name: Zalon Dirt
Zalon Dirt.description: A fertile soil that feeds by dissolving and absorbing insects and certain small animals. Most geologists believe it to have fine agricultural potential.

Rod of Brutality +10.name: Rod of Brutality +10
Rod of Brutality +10.description: A cylindrical rod with a complex dimpled surface. While it somewhat resembles a key, the Murderess’s first thought was how she could use it to pummel people. Suffice to say, she came up with the name.

Icarus Wings.name: Icarus Wings
Icarus Wings.description: An invention of Nopon who dreamed of taking to the skies. Shockingly ineffective, though that doesn't deter the many Nopon who optimistically plummet to their deaths each year.

Megajolt Rattle.name: Megajolt Rattle
Megajolt Rattle.description: Though it looks like a baby's trinket, the noise this rattle produces when shaken has the power to fell buildings. A Prospector named Ginger gave it its name, and it is currently being researched as a weapon.

Extra-large Cash Box.name: Extra-large Cash Box
Extra-large Cash Box.description: A piggy bank used by ancient Nopon. Legend claims that those who broke it open before it was full would have money trouble for the rest of their days.

Superior Scepter.name: Superior Scepter
Superior Scepter.description: An ornately decorated scepter, speculated to have once been utilized as a ceremonial piece for ancient nobility. Pathfinder H.B. thought it a perfect fit for himself and gave it this name.

Savage Sketch.name: Savage Sketch
Savage Sketch.description: A tablet depicting a scene of terror involving people fleeing from a dragon- like beast. Excited by this unknown creature that may or may not even exist, Prospector Vera came up with this name.

Iron Akebi Fruit.name: Iron Akebi Fruit
Iron Akebi Fruit.description: With a skin as tough as iron, this akebi is well equipped to surviving its harsh environment. Having existed for countless millennia, there is doubtless extremely vital genetic information dormant within.

Exalting Paint.name: Exalting Paint
Exalting Paint.description: A fluorescent paint used on the White Whale. A high phosphorescence gives it the ability to emit absorbed light without a reduction in intensity.

Oxygen Airbrake.name: Oxygen Airbrake
Oxygen Airbrake.description: A braking mechanism that ran on pure oxygen. It could also be weaponized for battle situations if necessary.

Spatial Control Jointer.name: Spatial Control Jointer
Spatial Control Jointer.description: A deceptively strong, yet compact, part for jointing and supporting large objects above the ground. Is currently used as a gravitational-control device.

Planter.name: Planter
Planter.description: A device that extracts water from rocks in order to aid the process of planetary terraforming. The discovery of Mira has rendered it somewhat pointless.

Rogebra Shockstone.name: Rogebra Shockstone
Rogebra Shockstone.description: This rock, formed in a lightning storm, stores lightning energy. It provides an electrical charge like a battery, but can be quite unstable.

Dithblade Fragment.name: Dithblade Fragment
Dithblade Fragment.description: Blade fragments from an alien Skell. Its materials exhibit properties of both great strength and extreme lightness. It also appears to contain a slight electrical charge.

Voltant Scanner.name: Voltant Scanner
Voltant Scanner.description: The panels on this item contain lamps that inform of any nearby toxins. As it requires alien-based technology to function, it doesn't seem to be usable by humans.

Book of Death and Rebirth.name: Book of Death and Rebirth
Book of Death and Rebirth.description: This book is worn to nigh unreadability, but the illustrations of giants depicted within feel somehow nostalgic. Letrick, the cathedral overseer, broke into tears upon seeing it and gave it this name.

Solar Wind Converter.name: Solar Wind Converter
Solar Wind Converter.description: This device captured gas released into space by stars and converted it into energy for use in the propulsion system.

Savage Claw.name: Savage Claw
Savage Claw.description: Specialized alien battle claws that appear to be used more as catalysts for energy- based attacks rather than for actual hand-to-hand fighting.

Autoposturizer.name: Autoposturizer
Autoposturizer.description: A posture-control apparatus that protects against spatial disorientation during interstellar journeys. Primarily used by crew members undertaking repair details outside the ship.

Cooling Lava.name: Cooling Lava
Cooling Lava.description: A fragrant form of lava that can be eaten once cooled. Though completely non-toxic, it still may be a while before the item appears on the menus of New LA's finer restaurants.

Charred Crock.name: Charred Crock
Charred Crock.description: A giant black vessel fashioned from lava. Said to have been constructed by a now- extinct civilization.

Lava Chestnut.name: Lava Chestnut
Lava Chestnut.description: A heat-resistant seed, often found in lava, that forms into fruit-bearing rock upon cooling. Though sweet and nutritious, it remains a tough nut to crack.

Capricious Kettle.name: Capricious Kettle
Capricious Kettle.description: A cauldron that billows with thick black smoke and is engraved from top to bottom with strange symbols. After discovering it, the Prospector Harvey gave it a fanciful name in hopes of selling it for big money.

Poron Tulip.name: Poron Tulip
Poron Tulip.description: A large pollen-filled flower known for its rapid expansion. The pollen is unusually appetizing, making it much sought after by the Nopon.

Zagyrin Cragstone.name: Zagyrin Cragstone
Zagyrin Cragstone.description: An organic steel forged in the heat of Cauldros's lava lakes. It boasts legendary hardness due to its many layers.

Jaharmum.name: Jaharmum
Jaharmum.description: A golden chrysanthemum that grows and reproduces by drifting on the winds of Cauldros, absorbing sulfur as it goes. Just before death, it takes on the form of a sulfur crystal.

Cliord Oil.name: Cliord Oil
Cliord Oil.description: This treasured red oil is found on Cauldros surfaces during rainy days. It looks eerily like a pool of blood to the naked eye.

Dark Lantern.name: Dark Lantern
Dark Lantern.description: A hand lamp that uses a secret Nopon oil formula to emit a beautiful light. Due to difficulties in producing the oil, such lanterns rarely shine anymore.

Shooting Firefly.name: Shooting Firefly
Shooting Firefly.description: After hatching, this larva ages and dies within the same day. Its rare glow is beautiful to observe.

Kyatara Onion.name: Kyatara Onion
Kyatara Onion.description: Peeling this onion's skin reveals an inedible middle. The subtly sweet taste of the outer layers, however, is something to be savored.

Gyulali.name: Gyulali
Gyulali.description: A fruit with a meaty taste. Heating brings about strange anomalies in its flavor, with high temperatures evoking beef, and low temperatures pork.

Brambloo Shoot.name: Brambloo Shoot
Brambloo Shoot.description: This may look like a tree, but it feels and tastes like bamboo. The fiercer indigens of Cauldros often use its outer cap to polish their fangs and tusks.

Mottled Mums.name: Mottled Mums
Mottled Mums.description: A fig with strong purification effects that thrives even in bad soil. So strong are its  effects that it has the ability to diminish vital nutrition if taken without cause.

Nightmare Pineapple.name: Nightmare Pineapple
Nightmare Pineapple.description: A black pineapple dotted with eyelike reticules. Those who touch it are said to be sent into a fit of nightmares. Only recommended for the strong of mind.

Dulcet Goose.name: Dulcet Goose
Dulcet Goose.description: A bird resembling the humble Earth goose, but with an entrancing angelic call. This good-natured bird will use its voice to guide others out of harm's way.

Pan-analysis Chips.name: Pan-analysis Chips
Pan-analysis Chips.description: An item able to view and detect the entire range of electromagnetic waves, including infrared. It is also able to stand in for microscopes and telescopes.

Sharpening Stone.name: Sharpening Stone
Sharpening Stone.description: A hard stone carved into the shape of a hammer and used in construction. For some reason, the whole tool is carved from stone—not just the head.

Autiga Powder.name: Autiga Powder
Autiga Powder.description: While this appears to be a powder, it behaves more like a plant. It can often be found clinging to rocks, much like a form of moss.

Octopus Regulator.name: Octopus Regulator
Octopus Regulator.description: A remote-controlled body featuring several limbs protruding from a spherical center. It is of particular use for those conducting sensitive operations in the vacuum of space.

Belzadozebu Scallions.name: Belzadozebu Scallions
Belzadozebu Scallions.description: A poisonous black root that can kill even the largest of creatures. If left unchecked, it eventually ends its own existence as deadly toxins spread throughout its cells.

Gibney Jackal.name: Gibney Jackal
Gibney Jackal.description: A rare species only found in Cauldros. At first glance it may be mistaken for a wolf—though its fearsome ruby eyes can be seen for miles.

Abyssal Cricket.name: Abyssal Cricket
Abyssal Cricket.description: A huge red insect that shoots fire from its mouth, often igniting natural gas spumes in the process. It is the prime suspect in many unexplained explosions.

Chrampoline.name: Chrampoline
Chrampoline.description: A Nopon-sized trampoline made from a an elastic, rubberish material. Once used at festival time, it has since been banned after a slew of injuries and lawsuits.

Gun Snake.name: Gun Snake
Gun Snake.description: A snake-like reptile that subsists on iron ore. Its stomach contains mounds of undigested rocks that are used as bullets to keep approaching predators at bay.

Bogano Sleeping Bag.name: Bogano Sleeping Bag
Bogano Sleeping Bag.description: A fire-resistant, 20-foot-long sleeping bag woven from bogano weed. Originally made by giants, but now used as a yurt by grateful Nopon.

Bullet Fly.name: Bullet Fly
Bullet Fly.description: A tough-bodied and incredibly fast fly. Getting in their way will likely result in serious injury, so be careful when wandering the wilds of Cauldros.

Stone Lens.name: Stone Lens
Stone Lens.description: A polished, transparent stone often used as a lens. Nopon also value it for its ability to start fires.

Cetecegem Beetle.name: Cetecegem Beetle
Cetecegem Beetle.description: A very large beetle that can reach over three feet in length. It will imbibe and expel large volumes of water whenever threatened.

Charged Cayenne.name: Charged Cayenne
Charged Cayenne.description: A chili pepper infused with the energy of lightning, guaranteed to bring even the strongest to their knees. It's more at home in the arms industry than a kitchen.

Demon Boar.name: Demon Boar
Demon Boar.description: A five-eyed, boar-like beast. Despite its demonic appearance, it is surprisingly timid—often fleeing in terror at the sight of the smallest insect.

Prickly Cricket.name: Prickly Cricket
Prickly Cricket.description: An energetic cricket that is always busy stockpiling food. It attacks if disturbed, especially if it comes in contact with its nemesis—the vagabond ant.

Lava Fox.name: Lava Fox
Lava Fox.description: A fox-like creature that draws nutrition from lava. Any other liquid will result in instant death, so their numbers tend to fall considerably after heavy downpours.

Bogano Weed.name: Bogano Weed
Bogano Weed.description: A hardy plant that refuses to burn even in the fiery rains of Cauldros. It is, however, extremely sensitive to cold.

Muranadium.name: Muranadium
Muranadium.description: No wildlife—or species—can resist the charms of this plant. Harvested almost to extinction by the ancient Mirans, now it can only be found deep inside Cauldros.

Elemental Battery.name: Elemental Battery
Elemental Battery.description: This device transforms airborne particles into electrical power, ensuring an almost inexhaustible supply of energy. It seems to have been used as a weapon by certain alien races.

Mega Muscle Builder.name: Mega Muscle Builder
Mega Muscle Builder.description: A shock-absorbing component that seems to have been used in ancient automatons. The Interceptor Giotto used it as exercise equipment and gave it a name to suit his personal tastes.

FN Prototype 3.name: FN Prototype 3
FN Prototype 3.description: One of the prototype models created during the development of FrontierNav. Not as advanced as the data probes currently in use, but not a bad effort.

Doom Mask.name: Doom Mask
Doom Mask.description: Seemingly both mechanical and organic, this mask-shaped object has the ability to absorb bodily fluids. The Outfitter Alexa gave it its name in a fit of excitement.
